,Recommended,322500,21778160,"Posted: 11 March, 2016",all,cheese.9898,"The most common complaint about this game (and the only one I've heard) is that the story mode is much too short.And yes, I'd have to agree there: The game can be ""beaten"" in under 2 hours.HOWEVER, people don't seem to be taking all the other additions of the game into account, such as secrets, challenges, and endless arenas.With all of the above included, I can't see the problem.I suppose if you are looking for hours and hours of story, then I don't recommend this game (the story isn't its strongest point anyways).However, if you're looking for a game that you can just casually come back to whenever you feel like having a good time, then I feel that this game is perfect for that.I rate this game: 7.8/10(I'm hoping they eventually decide to implement the Steam workshop to extend the game's length even further)"
,Recommended,322500,21467292,"Posted: 25 February, 2016",all,76561198002511762,"You know that one guy that logs into the FPS and just kills everyone by himself? So you eventually just have to leave the server because no one can kill him and things are getting hostile since it's no fun for anyone but him and now people are raging about hacks that may or may not exist?Well now you can be that guy!________________________________________Just an add on for the top reviews saying the game is too short, I spent 2-3 hours on the story, I've spent 7-8 hours so far on the modes I unlocked after beating story and I've still not gotten to unlocking all the endless arenas or challanges. So I'm just going to respectfully disagree with the price not being worth it.The BULK of the game and its unlockables appears to be after you beat the story line.________________________________________Lots of arguments going on about this game, since I've somehow ended up as a top review I'll go ahead and expand further on why I think the game is worth the price with things I've said in the comments.The story is just a  prelude to the meat of the game, a fabric to wrap the metagame of the arena/arcade shooter in. Why you're doing this seemingly pointless task of killing red guys, the sort of world you're fighting in, etc.The story itself doesn't flat out tell you much either, even after you beat it you still have to piece things together by explore the menus, hidden features, chat logs, and there's also secrets and hidden terminals on each level of the campaign that let you access more lore/chat logs... something to go back and find after you've beaten them once.But in the end much like in a fighting game you're really just here for the mechanics anyway, so buy it for that and you shouldn't be disappointed."
