,Not Recommended,322500,24807240,"Posted: 10 August, 2016",all,Gunmetal Buffalo,"Ehh.For 25 bucks, you get a handful of levels and then another handful to unlock and play in endless mode.I'm writing this at 2.4 hours played. I would estimate that 2 hours were spent on the ""story"" mode, and the other ~30 minutes were spent messing around with the first few ""endless"" levels.By the end of that play session, I was pretty much done with SuperHot. The novelty had worn off, the story mode was complete, and none of the extras or replays were going to keep me around.If you see this game on sale, or get a coupon, I'd say go for it. It's an interesting mechanic to play with. At full price, I'd tell you to save your money. In the meantime, try and track down the original Superhot. It's about the same length, it's free, and I actually preferred the story in that one over this one.It's not a bad game, and it's a game I can honestly say I enjoyed both times I played it, but it's right on the borderline of things I'd recommend. I don't regret my purchase at full price, but I don't think the average user is going to feel the same way."
