,Not Recommended,322500,21471274,"Posted: 26 February, 2016",all,Neuf,"This was not a decision I made lightly. It's a bit of a shame that Steam reviews only have a thumbs up or thumbs down, not any sort of in-between score.I expect that fans of the game will downvote the hell out of this review for not recommending it.Truth is I'm a huge fan of this game. Despite a couple technical hiccups (which may not be actual bugs, given the nature of the game), the game is ridiculously fun and stylish as hell. Though SUPERHOT has really only one gameplay gimmick, it never grew stale. Killing a room full of red guys in impossible situations never got boring, and the game's narrative actually kept me very engaged.Since time only moves when you do, the game feels very far away from any other first person shooter made before it. It's impossible to run-and-gun, you need to carefully plan your steps to dodge deadly projectiles, while also aiming carefully and lining up those perfect shots; with so little ammo, you can't afford to be careless. It's the freshest breath of air an FPS fan has been able to inhale for the last long while.So why am I not recommending this incredible game?The price.I've defended games like Jazzpunk and McPixel, even Undertale, when faced with the criticism of a game being too short. I truly believe it's about the experience. But SUPERHOT has pushed my limit.$35 Canadian dollars for a game you can potentially beat in a few hours?It's not quite worth it.SUPERHOT is amazing. But $35 is a very steep price for a quick game. I suppose there is replay value in the Endless Mode, trying to do sections more efficiently, and trying to uncover the game's secrets. But really, as excellent and fun as it may be, there is no variation in gameplay.Tons of AAA titles boast campaigns that barely register 6 hours and they cost twice as much, I know this. But, having paid a much smaller price for games I felt carried more weight, I still don't think SUPERHOT has a justifiable price.If it came down in a sale or something I'd push this game onto every person within reach and earshot of me.SUPERHOT is an incredibly creative and well-crafted game.It just costs too much right now."
,Not Recommended,322500,21540300,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,Bäle,"I can't recommend it or not. The core gameplay is great, but there are a lot of problems. If you like the demo and would like to play with variations on it on ~25 levels, go for it. An extra gameplay mechanic gets chucked in halfway to spice things up a little.It's a lot like Portal in that it's a small, short puzzlish game with an excellent, original atmosphere and style, but it's nowhere near as polished.Story is compelling and fun, but only 2 hours long. Half of the challenge modes are good, half are garbage, there's about 12 in total. Endless mode is fun but you don't have any rewards or goals. Time-trial mode is the same. What sealed the deal for me continuing to play was the secret-finding exploration mode.It's fun to start up and play one or two levels for 5mins.Add a level editor and proper way to share them and this would be solid gold.~~~ Here's all the problems that should be easily fixed ~~~Endless modes and time-trial modes are lack-luster; it doesn't compare scores against friends or give rankings/grades. Stupidly, the first ~1.5 seconds of in-game time occur with the loading screen still up, so you have to begin blindly to get the best times, not that there is anything motivating you to improve your time past the single goal they give. Endless mode is fun, but the game gives you no milestones to aim for - all of the unlockables (timed endless modes) are unlocked by total kills ever rather than top score.Irredeemable bugs:There's a minigame that doesn't stop the music on exiting, leaving it looping over itself and forcing a restart. Some achievements are bugged, including giving me the ""complete all time trials"" achievement when I only did 5 of them. Worst of all, completion of the last level you do before quitting IS RANDOMLY NOT SAVED SO YOU HAVE TO DO IT AGAIN.Graphics:The brightness can be a bit difficult to look at sometimes.Animations are janky, which is a bit weird because they literally only have one animated model.It is also somehow jittery at times? VSync is broken and doesn't lock to 60fps. Level 21 is very laggy for no apparent reason.Settings menu is pitiful, you have about 3 graphics options and can't change key bindings.Gameplay:Thrown objects will very occasionally bounce off or pass through enemies for no apparent reason.Thrown objects move faster than bullets. If you shoot and immediately throw a gun, the bullet hits the gun.I don't know why they don't have time completely stop, it makes for a much more precise experience.When you land from a jump the screen gets a pointless and annoying/disorienting shock effect.You can't really tell how much ammo your gun has left, reducing your ability to plan stuff.The gun reload animation is ♥♥♥♥♥♥ and you can't tell how long it has left until you can fire again.The end-of-level replays aren't quite satisfying enough, they're still too slow.If an enemy breaks something too close to themselves they get stunned, which is a bit lame."
