76561198008198805,Recommended,322500,31435099,Posted: 29 April,all,Joachim,"What a gem i discovered. Really loved this game, great indie FPS game. This game relies solely on gameplay and doesn't have realistic high tech visuals, nor any particular interesting storyline. It's just you in different white environments with red dudes as villain. Weapons are shotgun, pistol, rifle, katana, bat.Time moves only when you moves. You can jump, stun enemies by throwing weapons or objects against them.The story mode is short, like 2 hours or so and if it was only that it would certainly be overpriced. Endless mode is a bit grindy and the goal is to get a certain kills on a map before you unlock the next map. Fun is trying to get as many kills as possible before getting overwhelmed and killed.Now the best stuff are the challenges, which make you complete all levels on certain criteria, like with katana or throwables only, time based, or completing all levels in one go without dying. Had real fun going for those. There's one specific level that is hard, called Elevator and that one really gave me some irritation when going for the norestart challenge. Just buy it on a sale, the game is a lot of fun and a bit like a shooter puzzle. Recommended."
