,Recommended,322500,24100997,"Posted: 4 July, 2016",all,jiminywinkle,"SUPERHOT ReviewPLOTBasically you're a dude on his computer talking to one of his online friends who sends him a cracked file for ""superhot.exe"" which is described as ""a tool"" by a company the game is being controlled by. Matrix-Inception♥♥♥♥♥♥happens and you get brainwashed. I would add extra info but I don't want to spoil it.GAMEPLAYNot inculding the massive ammounts of secrets and extra stuff to look at in the menus (including ""the game of life"" and other retro computer things), the game basically focuses on the player who is trying to eliminate all of the ""red dudes"" in each level using a variety of melee and ranged weapons. The main gimmick is that the level (including enemies and flying objects) only move at the same speed the player is moving at. The game is actually extremely fast-paced, which can be seen in the replays after a level, but what would be extreme difficulty and a need for inhuman reflexes is solved by the slowing mechanic, making you seem like a ♥♥♥♥ing ninja at the normal speed (so much so that they have a website just for uploading replays).PROS-Smooth mechanics-Insane visuals (especially in cinematics)-Developer support-(limited) VR support-Full controller support-Nice arsenal of weapons-Hard but fair (mostly)-4th wall breaks that play in with the story-Fun overallCONS-Minimal enemy noise for footsteps and other motions (expect to be screwed over quite a bit)-Story could be a little less cryptic-Short (I have no issues with the length due to the tons of extra tidbits and gamemodes to do, but it is a major problem with some people) [See ""OUTDATED ISSUES""]-You have to be looking directly at an enemy to melee-Minimum distance to body switch is tricky-Can get repetitive-Overpriced at the momentOUTDATED ISSUES-Lots of people have been talking about the fact that you can't see your replay without ""SUPER HOT"" flashing in your screen, but pressing f5 gets rid of it, and there are lots of playback options to use with a numpad. If this has been here the whole time I don't understand what people are whining about. (BTW fn+f5 or fn+alt+f5 to do it on Mac)-Everyone has been talking about the length of the game, but the developers have recently announced a free DLC which includes extra levels, procedural generation, skill-based powerups, and other goodies which are being said to drastically increase the playtime of the game."
