,Not Recommended,322500,28699383,"Posted: 26 December, 2016",all,вражеский танк,"Tedious and frustrating. Enemies are constantly spawning in behind you, so you have to look around all the time to make sure you're not going to get shot in the back. However, looking around also causes time to move, making you more likely to get shot. Dodging bullets is made tricky by the fact that it's hard to get a sense of how wide your body is. In most of the levels, the most effective strategy is simply to back yourself into a corner so that nobody can spawn behind you, and then dodge left and right as you get shot at; this is especially effective if you can find a pillar to stand behind. The harder levels are purely a matter of trial-and-error and memorization of spawn locations. It only took me two hours to finish the story, but even that felt too long. It's a cool concept, but the execution is just not up to par."
