,Recommended,322500,21931589,"Posted: 19 March, 2016",all,Misery,"Obligatory line:  This is the most innovative shooter I've played in years!There, now that I've done as the game clearly orders me to (literally), I can get to the actual review.SUPERHOT (no, I dont know why it's always capitalized, just roll with it) is basically ""Bullet Time: The Game"".  The core mechanic is that time only moves when you do.  When you're just turning your view around, it'll move kinda slowly, but when you're actually MOVING, it'll be real-time. But the instant you stop... back to time-stop.  When combined with the fact that bullets dont move at the speed they do IRL... and are slowed down just enough that even in real-time, you can follow their path (they are still very quick though), you can watch enemy shots, and dodge out of the way, just like in the Matrix!  But if that were the only mechanic this offered, it wouldnt be nearly as interesting.Needless to say, the other core mechanic is, well, the weapons.  There are only a few of these... pistol, shotgun, machinegun, katana, bat.  Not much, you say?  Believe me, it's enough.  Learning all of the properties of these weapons is key, not just for using them yourself, but for dealing with enemies.  With the game's bright, stark graphics, it's super easy to see at a glance what each enemy is carrying, and plan accordingly.  But shooting and slashing isnt your only trick.  You can also fling weapons or objects at enemies; hit them with one, and they'll be stunned, and their weapon will go flying... and you can grab it right out of the air, if you are in position.  Then let 'em have it!  Just as fun as it sounds.That's not all though:  The game's other mechanic is the HotSwitch, the ability to instantly, and from any distance, switch into the body of any enemy you can see.  Did a guy with a shotgun just fire an unavoidable wall of bullets at you?  Take him over before they hit.  The only downside is that when you take someone over, the weapon they are holding will break; but you can bypass this by smacking them with an object so they drop it, taking them over, and then grabbing the gun that'll be hanging in the air right next to you.Oh, and you can slash, or even SHOOT, enemy bullets out of the air.Combine all of these things, and, well... it cant get much more awesome than this.Be warned though:  This is NOT a story-focused game.  Oh, it has one, and it's interesting, but it's very short.  This is more of an arcade-style score-attack game, as the meat of the game's content... and there's alot of it... is in the ""endless"" mode.  Dont think this makes the game not worth the cost though, because it is.Also:  This game is HARD.  You're going to die.  A lot.  Enemies are extremely numerous, fast, aggressive, smart, and can grab weapons off of the ground. And you have to really pay attention, as they just... keep... coming.  You have to constantly check the doors for the tell-tale red glow that signifies an enemy about to spawn from one (and they can act *instantly* after they spawn, so dont think you have a safe moment while they're doing so!). But this just makes all of your awesome actions even more amazing, when you're successful against them.  But yeah, if you're after a challenge... you'll find it here.Really, I cant recommend this one enough.  An FPS that rewards careful, tactical play, yet still requires LOTS of real skill to do well in, with awesome mechanics that let you do ridiculously awesome moves, and never any true unfairness... really, it doesnt get much better than this.  I'll be playing this one alot, myself.Oh, and one more thing:  After any run, you can view, edit, and even upload a real-time replay of everything that just happened.  I honestly just never get tired of watching these."
