76561197969417125,Recommended,322500,26569531,"Posted: 12 November, 2016",all,G00N3R,"Superhot is a first person shooter built around a unique mechanic - time only moves when you do.The gameplay is really fun. A typical sequence of events will see you decapitate an enemy with your katana, throw the katana at another enemy, catch his gun in mid air, turn around, see a bullet slowly inching towards your head, side step the bullet and shoot the next guy, throw your gun at someone else to stun them, catch their gun and kill them with it ... all in the space of about 10 seconds of ""real time"".Its almost like a turn based strategy game. When you're surrounded by multiple enemies and feeling like ""oh crap, I'm about to die"", you can slow the action right down and take a few moments to devise a plan to survive. You feel like such a powerful badass, like Neo in The Matrix (the first one, not the terrible sequels).Its just a shame that the game is really short. I finished the ""story"" in less than 2 hours (101 minutes to be exact). And that story is extremely basic. There aren't any interesting characters or dialogue. Its really just a collection of around 30 short levels where your only goal is to kill all the enemies. The bulk of the game requires you to replay the same levels over and over and over again in various endless and challenge modes, chasing high scores. Having got most of the achievements in about 8 hours, I'm already feeling a lack of motivation to continue.The graphics are very stylish, the environments are all white and grey, enemies are bright red, and weapons are dark black. This also has a positive impact on the gameplay - important objects are immediately visible, which helps you make split second tactical decisions. Controls work great with mouse and keyboard, and I didn't encounter any bugs, but there is a noticeable lack of music. And the AI isn't particularly smart. Enemies mostly just run straight towards you, and if you find some good cover, you can totally exploit their stupidity (I have scores of 55 and 80 on a couple of endless levels).I'd definitely recommend playing Superhot, but I think its best to wait for a sale. I bought it for 40% off, which feels like a fair price. I also hope the developers will make a sequel that takes the core gameplay and expands on it with more weapons, enemy types, levels, etc"
76561198017320637,Recommended,322500,33668385,Posted: 20 July,all,Bongo,"Superhot is a very fun, original game that provides more than you'd expect, including a story and extra gamemodes. However, for the current price I'm not sure if you are getting your money's worth in terms of content. I still recommend the game, but maybe moreso when it is on sale."
