,Recommended,322500,21539624,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,MisterSir.toot,"I don't really write reviews for games but I feel like I should write one for this, specifically since it is in Early Access.Yes, the story is very short, unfortunately. I completed it in about 2 hours, with messing around in the campaign (Trying dumb stuff, no slow mo, etc). While it is a pretty dark and good story (If you want to call it a story, more like a stretched plotline to a story), there really isn't much to it.After beating the story you get Challenge Mode, and Endless Mode. Challenge Mode being the single player campaign with certain restrictions or objectives to meet, Endless Mode being exactly that. endless enemies spawning in an arena. The more you play, the more arenas you unlock. It can get boring after a while but I can see myself always coming back for at least a little fun for quite some time in the future.The game itself, however, is fantastic. It even came with it's own website, where you can upload your own clips and replays. While even that may not be handling all the traffic it's been getting, not many games have that. I do wish there were more edit options, however.Time moving only when you move is a great concept. Any action, even rotating, allows things to move. You can chain together kills in a very satisfying way and put together combos that make you look like you've played shooters every day for your entire life. The game flows extremely smooth and I can't help but say the only reason it wasn't worth the 20 dollars is because the story is so short. But I'm sure more content will be added in future patches, so eventually it will be worth the 20. 15? Sure, but personally I think 10 is too low.With the popularity this has gotten in only a few days time, there is bound to be more content added (hopefully some *background music*) and eventually, I would hope, mod support. Community levels I would imagine is the minimum that will come into play.Play this game, tell people to play this game, share it with your friends.But don't talk too much about it, don't let them know what the system is about."
