76561197970649200,Recommended,322500,21541536,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,danpaladin,"This game is great.  What a breath of fresh air.  The base gameplay feels like nothing else I've ever played.  This is action that has all kinds of craziness to it at a pace that is slowed down a little bit more than enough to barely be able to deal with it all.  Time only moves when you do, but you're still under constant pressure and constant fire.  Throwing guns at people to take their other guns from them, dodging bullets, grabbing a telephone and whipping it at the incoming bullets to destroy that oncoming shotgun blast, switching bodies to the guy behind the machine gunner giving you trouble and punching him in the head, etc etc etc..The campaign is great, but it's just the warm-up.  Once it is completed there are Endless modes and Challenges to complete and unlock.  The first to unlock is a Katana-Only set of what you already know, but you're unable to use anything but the Katana you started with.  Switches up every strategy I had formed prior.  I found myself learning new tricks the whole way.  My friends and I have been switching off every couple runs in an attempt to unlock everything and even after 13 hours we still haven't unlocked it all yet.There's a couple minigames hiding in here, like Tree Dude, which can be fun if you're in the mood for something simple.I don't think the price is too high, and I don't think the campaign is too short (since it's really just at tutorial, sort of).  This the most innovative shooter I've played in years!"
