,Not Recommended,322500,30804205,Posted: 28 March,all,SpaceCouncil,"For the sake of brevity..Genre tags:FPS, Puzzle, ExperimentalValue Proposition:I feel this game is very polarizing, a modern cult classic if you will. It's short, around 2 hours but has an endless mode upon completion.BSERC- (Borderline Sardonic and Extremely Reductive Comparison): To be honest.. Games similar to this will be called SUPERHOT clones. But since we are here. 'Receiver' and 'Sword with Sauce' are relatively similar.Concomitant Exposition and SummationSUPER HOT SUPER HOT…..SUPER…HOTI did not like this game. I did not enjoy it at any single instance or as a complete package.Now, the game is visually striking, gorgeous even. However the actual play is very lackluster, its needlessly frustratingNOTdifficult-- frustrating. If not moving, the game is essentially slowed to a near pause. Moving at all or taking action makes everything go full speed. You will die often and you will die fast. This is a puzzle game at its very core. One that is solved by appropriately leading enemies and making efficient use of the items within your immediate vicinity whilst dodging bullets.You can punch or throw items to knock weapons out of enemies hands and then use them or use the ones found on the ground. I'll never understand why they left out being able to crouch or simply bend your neck. More often then not than not I found myself literally staring at a bullet once turned around slowly proceeding into my face that I had no course of action to prevent. Once again, I had to restart.The game takes place inside the EXTREMELY tired notion of being inside a computer. The setup is as such: Dude instant messages you, gets you into early access build of a game. Things are not what they seem. Between stages you must speak to him and tell him you what you think, these sections are obviously contrived but it makes you hit a bunch of keys on the keyboard anyways. Very... 'Cibele'-- 'Emily Is Away' of it. Of course with the added twist of something reminiscent of 'Pony Island'. The story is very mundane if a little disconcerting.The main issue is the game is it's not consistent. Grabbing items can be finicky and cost you too much time to get out of the way of bullet spray.  Not once did I feel as though I was triumphant for overcoming a great obstacle or challenge. I felt as though I had efficientlygamedmy way through a section to checkmark the next set ofgamingthe systems. You gain knowledge in each level if you're able to recall when enemy spawns are so as to be prepared. Throwing the weapon is often more useful than shooting it as it takes too long to ready the next shot. I just did not have fun figuring out the stages or feel I had accomplished anything. I simply felt relief when it was over.THE GISTLike I said, this is likely to be very polarizing. I think this game is unique for certain. But I cannot recommend. Maybe pick it up on sale should the premise still interest you. All that being said, it is indeed very unique but it just doesn't feel special; Far too frustrating for anyone not already very dedicated.Follow my curation page for more."
