,Recommended,322500,24240994,"Posted: 10 July, 2016",all,Cortina MK3,"Superhot is the sort of game that you want and don't even realize it.Superhot is an amazing game hands down, its very different from newer first-person shooters games that are coming out, instead of the quick-paced, ""Oh look at my gun skin, cost me £1200"" games that are out today, this goes in the opposite, giving you 3 guns to choose from, a pistol with 4-5 shots, a shotgun with 2-3 shots and a burst rifle that has 3 burst shots in it as well as some melee weapons like a katana (My choice of weapon) and a baseball bat or even your fists.Now there is two major components I currently haven't mentioned, 1) Time Stopping, 2) Body Stealing.Now the first one, time stopping, my favorite part of this game because it is entierly unique, in my 15 years of playing video games, I haven't come across anything like it, you move, the world moves, you stop, everything stops, giving you time to decide what you want to do as well as planning you actions and picking out who should die first.Now body stealing, another incredibly unique part of this game, allowing you to take the bodies of your enemies in order to get a better vantage point or even to get out of a sticky situation (I should say that this feature has saved my life more than a few times in playing this game). Now the downside to stealing a body is that if they have a weapon, they discard it, however, if you plan your movements with the time stop, this shouldn't be a problem, throw a weapon, it hits them, they drop theres and body steal, boom, you have there body and there weapons.Now the last thing I would like to talk about is the Campaign as well as the different gamemodes. The campaign is the most amazing campaign i've ever played, the way its starts out as just a friend basically saying ""Hey dude, play this game,"" and ending with, well I won't spoil it, but its brilliant, and in completing the campaign, you get to do the different gamemodes, my favorite being the endless game mode, with maps such as Office and Warehause, in which you're put into a room and just kill hoards and hoards of the red guys, using everything to stop or in this case, delay, your inevitable death.In conclusion, Superhot, even though i've played I think at this time around 20 hours, maybe less, this is my all-time favorite game I've ever played, its a unique experience, very basic but beautiful graphics and a game full of rage quits (I've had my fair share). I would definetly recommend buying this game, or if you are still unsure, watch some YouTubers such as Nerd3 or VineSauce Joel play it and you be the judge of it :)."
