76561198339884852,Recommended,322500,28196769,"Posted: 4 December, 2016",all,bbmink,"I absolutely loved SUPERHOT from the moment I started playing this game. It will take you back to when first person shooters were less about simulating real life combat and more about destroying the nameless opposition.The game is visually stunning with its basic black, white, and red minimalist colour scheme. The slow motion effect makes the game all that more artistically satisfying; SUPERHOT is more about the art of sniping than it is about run-and-gun chaos. Imagine a gun fight in which you can take in all the information around you before making the right move. By the end of the game, my aiming accuracy improved so dramatically that I was completing missions much more swiftly à la James Bond.I also appreciated the metanarrative where one is playing a game as one is stuck inside a game. In that sense, SUPERHOT shares something with Pony Island. The game is also replayable since beating it only unlocks more material. You'll want to beat your personal best in these new levels, which makes SUPERHOT a great game for the highscore-obsessed gamer--it reminds me of N++ that way.In short, buy this unique game; it's simple and complex, simultaneously. You'll be left repeating SUPERHOT! SUPERHOT! for hours once you start. Trust me on this..."
