76561198122944652,Recommended,322500,26242349,"Posted: 27 October, 2016",all,HE COOKIN'!!!!!,"Fun game, but, as pretty much everyone else says, feels very overpriced for such a short campaign. Wouldn't recommend paying more than 15 bucks.The gameplay obviously is brilliant. It's a puzzle game disguised as a shooter where time only moves when you do. Well actually, that isn't entirely true, it does move, just very, very slowly. What surprised me most was how incredibly challenging this game actually is. You'd think that being able to stop time and plan out every action would make every level a breeze, but the developers did a great job of making you really work for it. I didn't beat a single room on my first try.There is a bit of an attempt at some sort of plot/intrigue and its sort of interesting, but ends up being too vague to really be compelling. I would describe it as ""mildly interesting"" and nothing more. But hey, at least they tried.All in all, SuperHot feels like a very polished concept of something that could be so much bigger. I could definitely see a big triple A title being developed around the SuperHot time mechanic but with more realistic graphics and longer, more developed plot."
