76561198040989295,Recommended,322500,21801626,"Posted: 12 March, 2016",all,SmileyCraft,"I absolutely love this game man! Absolute gem! It is definately the most innovative game I've played in years! The best thing about this game is how badass it feels to complete a level and to then watch your replay.Quite some people seem to complain about the length of the game compared to the price. And even though I agree it should be a longer game considering the price, I don't mind at all! The replayability is definately there, especially because the developers added over ten challenge modes. These challenge modes are pretty interesting and most definately add a new challenge to the game! There also is an endless mode which is just as fun aswell. The game also has a lot of easter eggs which quite fun to discover. They are pretty rewarding aswell.I completely recommend this game, but it does have it's minor issues. The story mode is not all that interesting, and even though that wouldn't normally mind me, the fact that most of the 'cutscenes' are unskippable is very annoying. But this isn't that much of a problem, because after you finished the story mode once, you will never have any cutscenes again. And the majority of the fun I have had was after I completed the story.As for bugs, I have played this game a lot (like a LOT) and I have not been bothered with any bugs ever. Except for one bug, which is that the killstagram doesn't work (for me). The game allows you to save your replays and it is supposed to automatically upload your replay to killstagram, which is a website. But this isn't too big of a deal, because all the replays that you saved are still stored on your computer.In conclusion, the game is amazingly fun, maybe just a bit short, but that's only if you don't consider the great replayability. The unskippable cutscenes are annoying, but there aren't that many, so that's not a big deal.If you ask me, it would be a dream come true if Valve bought the game and created a SUPERHOT2, which would be just as amazing as Portal2!"
