,Recommended,322500,28938538,Posted: 2 January,all,Ducktor,"This review will be for both the standard version and the VR version (played with HTC Vive using ReVive)SUPERHOT:I was supposed to get this game for free as I backed the kickstarter for it, but I never got my key, so I had to buy it ""again"" for full price.SUPERHOT is an interesting take on the FPS genre where time only moves when you move, making you feel like you're in The Matrix when you dodge the bullets in slowmotion. It focuses on careful planning and situational awareness rather than the modern run 'n gun trend.After you've finished a level you will get a replay (which you can save) in real time which makes you feel even more awesome.Pros:Makes you feel like a badassLet's you review your play in real timeAddictingFun mechanicsCons:Limited FOVUnpredictable hitreg (sometimes you'll be fine, other times you will die)Very limited modsWay too shortConclusion:The game is fun and unique, but unfortunately the devs left it for dead. It's incredibly limited in terms of settings and just overpriced. I wouldn't buy this game unless it was on at least a 50% sale.SUPERHOT VR:I actually got this one for free because I backed the other one. Don't know if everyone who backed it got it for free or if it's because I didn't get the ""2D"" version for free.This was played on the HTC Vive usingReVivewhich emulates the Oculus Rift (and Touch) so that you can play Oculus exclusive games on the Vive.SUPERHOT VR surprised me with the quality. The price is 25€ and it's not available on Steam yet (they are working on a Vive version, no ETA yet) so they didn't go too crazy on the pricing (VR games have a tendency to be incredibly expensive for the quality, limited audience and all), that being said it's still a bit pricy given the content offered.The VR version is a lot more polished than the 2D version. The controls are really buggy where the grip sometimes isn't registered and you drop an item too soon, but that might be a bug with ReVive since the game isn't designed for the Vive controllers. Other than that it's very stable.Pros:ImmersiveGreat teleportation systemAddictingBetter than the original in every wayCons:Way too shortPricyOculus exclusive (can get around with ReVive, wouldn't buy it either way)No moddingConclusion:This is the way SUPERHOT was meant to be played. Right there in the game (which is a game in a game, oh right there's a story in this as well) with full control of your movement. It's not as ""free"" as the 2D version was since VR is still in the awkward movement system where you pretty much have to use teleportation to keep the immersion, but SUPERHOT VR does this really well by having each level have small sections. The teleportation isn't as instant as most other VR games, instead it will fade the world in and out in a pace taht doesn't screw with your mind. You don't get sick from it and you still have enough room to walk around a bit (depending on your setup of course)."
