,Recommended,322500,28905843,Posted: 1 January,all,Cro,"TL;DR: If scoring and challenges are for you, then you will love SUPERHOT, otherwise you will be sorely disappointed.I was skeptical about this at first after seeing an abundance of negative reviews about the length of SUPERHOT, but I gave it a shot after a friend's recommendation.This is a scoring and challenge game, which I typically find short and similar to an arcade game. The extended hours of fun come from completing the challenge levels (katana-only, fists-only, fullstop, real-time, etc.) and going for speed records (speed run challenges). You will often find games like this in the following categories: shumps/shooting games, so-called rogue likes, and indie platformers. As an aside, I saw similar negative reviews for ""House of the Dying Sun,"" a tactics/space FPS game, criticizing the length, but neglecting the challenges.SUPERHOT is graphically simple, which helps to make important things pop out (enemies, bullets, and weapons), but is stylish enough to be interesting to look at.Sound is slowed down with time, which provides an indicator of enemies and bullets outside of your view. The glass shattering sounds are fairly satisfying as well.Overall, I enjoy this simple yet challenging game."
