,Recommended,322500,27381359,"Posted: 24 November, 2016",all,IOUS D,"Though very intrigued and excited for the unique gameplay this title was boasting, I grew hesitant to purchase SUPERHOT at full price once I caught wind of its very short campaign. Convinced I would not enjoy playing challenge modes enough to justify the cost, I held off for a couple weeks. However, my desire to actually play with the mechanics that had peaked my interest in the first place won out and I found myself emptying my Steam wallet.Contrary to my presumptions, I thoroughly enjoy the various modes this game has to offer, with plans on playing them periodically till the day I feel the icy grip of Death around me. Where the real payoff lain, though, was in the compaign, brief as it is. While I unabashedly indulge in AAA titles, I found myself more fulfilled by the one or two hours it took to complete the story mode of SUPERHOT, due to its uniqueness, and felt I had gotten my money's worth.If one enjoys classic sci-fi stories that breach the fringe of reality and implicitly ask philosophical questions, then this game is worth your time for the story alone. Beyond that, hours of entertainment can easily be achieved in the other game modes, most notably the Endless Mode."
