,Not Recommended,322500,33388790,Posted: 8 July,all,Naxza,"Two hours worth of content- if that- to be told ""hey, get your friends to buy this game,"" an endless mode (that you've probably exhausted in twenty minutes trying to exert the illusion of choice on the final level), the ability to replay levels (prolly take you half the time to do this time around) and some challenge mode.Don't get me wrong, the game is neat. The aesthetic is nice, gameplay handles well, replays look cool when done right. But every level is about the size of a small apartment unit, there's maybe only four ways to handle any conflict, the plot's kind of spastic (and a little abusive), and any sense of closure you get is actually, and I kid you not, literally telling you to tell your friends to buy the game.I was perhaps a little harsh in my first assessment, though- Levels are fun enough to repeat a few times, there's a few secret this-and-thats to find and/or unlock, the extra widgets outside of the main game itself are marginally neat if you're not expecting anything, yadda yadda. You can milk the two hours of content pretty far if you're a completionist or achievement hunter.I'd say buy it for ten bucks max, but I don't think SuperHOT's ever gone on sale that far. I don't think there's any promises for extra content or a level editor at this rate anyways. It's worth a romp if money's no object, I suppose. But not like this."
