,Recommended,322500,21480281,"Posted: 26 February, 2016",all,Abraxas,Puzzle FPS by way of The Matrix.
,Recommended,322500,21499400,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,DarthLukan,"SUPERHOT may just be one of the most fun games ever made! I have only had time to try out the first few levels which are pretty much tutorials, but holy crap is it awesome. There are lots of FPS puzzle games, but not like this. There isn't a puzzle in the level that you solve to move forward, the whole level is a puzzle and you're one of the pieces, so are all of the bullets and mobs. The time mechanic is great, it reminds me of an old game I used to play as a kid called ""Robots"" on Linux. You had a level which was a grid, nothing moves until you do, and the object of the game was to use the level to destroy the robots, as every time you move, they close in on you. SUPERHOT's a bit different as the mobs are closing in, but they are shooting at you which means that you have to dodge them, their bullets, and compesnate your aim so that your bullets find their mark too (since the mobs will try to dodge them). Obviously there's also the major difference of SUPERHOT being an FPS as well as having an awesome even if simple art style. An excellent job all around on this one!The menu system and interaction is great too. When I saw the retro terminal interface I was immediately transported back to my early childhood where the command line was your only interface to the system.Great job SUPERHOT Team!"
