,Not Recommended,322500,24357468,"Posted: 16 July, 2016",all,crowbar,"I thought people complaining about the lack of content are wrong, but they were so right. If this game had depth and varied gameplay, then the challenge and endless modes could keep one motivated for a longer time, but honestly the game isn't much fun in my opinion. ""The most innovative shooter I've played in years"" is a clever marketing gag at best, but it definitly isn't what this game is. The gameplay idea is neat, but nothing amazing and considering the demo version of this game and the time between that and the final release, not much has happened since then.I expected this game to have a very fluid combat system, where the player gets into a flow and rythm and feels cool and badass, but in reality the gameplay just drags on and feels clonky. To play optimally, you have to stop and move very small distances all the time, it is not easy to describe for me, but it feels like playing a racing simulator with the keyboard.It doesn't help that the animations look and feel clonky too and are of bad quality.That is even more apparent when the game shows you your completed mission at normal speed, where you can clearly see the poor animation quality, which results in poor player feedback and controls that feel unresponsive. The game has a cool artstyle and there are moments which are spectacular, but even the death animation of the enemies gets old really fast, partly because I think they aren't actually physics based, but pre-made animations, so they look the same all the time, but maybe that's just me.It is not that fun to shoot the weapons, it is definitly not fun to use melee weapons or throwables. Another factor for that is the TERRIBLE sound design. Weapons and melee weapons sound terrible, especially the sound when you punch an enemy is just weird. All these factors hurt the flow and rythm of the game, which makes it not very enjoyable for me. Yes, I could play in a way where I have more ""flow"", but then I'm intentionally playing worse to make the game more fun to play, which is stupid.I don't know what the developers could do to improve the problems I have, except having more budget and time, and higher production value, but after completing the game I lost all motivation to do anything further. The story was interesting, but doesn't gave me anything, it was just an excuse for playing random levels. And again, that would be okay, if the gameplay wasn't so dull and unresponsive."
