76561198107035007,Recommended,322500,30684852,Posted: 23 March,all,minimati,"__________________________________________________________________________________IF YOU DONT WANT LITTLE SPOILERS DONT READ THIS!!!!---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------Facts:Finished in: 3.1 hoursRating: 9________________________________________________________________________________To start off, well done to Piotr Iwanicki and the SUPERHOT team!The game plays incredibly well and all the controls are simple to learn and use (wasd, e, Mouse r, Mouse l). The game runs incredibly smoothly, and it is extremely staisfying to hear the glass breaking sound and seeing the red enemies break into tens of pieces. The game is also able to run quite well on lower end laptops (Macbook Pro 13 inch mid 2014 with no graphics card) however, for the best experience I suggest a proper PC.The idea of the game is why most people are going to be interested in it, if you dont move time doesnt move. Simple, right? At the start you can run around the map like in any other shooter just for the bants, but as you go further on the game becomes more challenging, and you begin to need more concentration. The maps also vary nicely as there are some on trains, subways and offices.The story was very interesting in my opinion. [SPOILERS AHEAD ----- YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED _ If you dont want spoilers on the story skip down to where it says ending of spoilers]. Your friend invites you to play a game, you play the game, the game tries to get you to not play the game, the game takes over your life, the game destroys your friendship, and in the end the game tells you that you are worthless and has you kill yourself. Now I know that that is very basic, but I dont want to ruin the whole story.In addition to this rather simple story, I believe that it has a deeper meaning. By attempting to kill the in-game you the red enemies were attemptint to protect you from having the game control your mind, through telling you that your body is holding you back. So are the red men your enemies in the game, or are you your own enemy. Its up to you to decide this, but I found this an interesting perspective to look at the game.[SPOILERS END HERE][SPOILERS END HERE][SPOILERS END HERE][SPOILERS END HERE]Overall, SUPERHOT is a fantastic first person shooter, with a unique idea and a plot that leaves you thinking. I would defineatly recomennd this game to anyone who plays on Steam, and would say that its almost a must play game.The only reason this game doesnt receive a 10/10 is because the price is simply too high. I finished the game in three hours and I took my time with it, returning to a few levels to retry different ways to beat the level.If the game is on sale, everyone should defineatly atleast try it.:)"
