76561198047533721,Recommended,322500,21507625,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,I_am_Trashman,"❗🔥❗🔥❗🔥❗🔥❗🔥 SUPER HOT SÜPER H0Т 👌 this ✔ game is ❗🔥❗🔥SUPER HOT ❗🔥❗🔥 SUPER ❗ HOT 🔥 Hi 👋 Friend, 👉 you 👈 have to ✔✔check👀out ✔✔ this 🎮 ɢąme. It is 👌 the most 💯 INNOVATIVE shooter 🔫💥 (chorus: ᴵᴺᴺᴼᵛᴬᵀᴵᵛᴱ) I've played 👍 in YEARS 📅. SUPER HOT! ❗🔥SUPER HOT! ❗🔥SUPER HOT! ❗ᵗʳᵉᵉ🎄ᵈᵘᵈᵉ🔥SUPER HOT! ❗🔥 ❗❗❗❗🔥🔥🔥❗❗🔥👍🔫💥🎮🎄🎮 🎮 ☠✔✔ ✔✔ innovativeUPDATE: So Superhot has some problemsProblem 1: In the latest patch they changed the movement speed to what feels almost 2x as fast as it used to be. This makes basic movement and dodging much more difficult and way less satisfying in general. Enemies can now move much more within even a brief key tap. This can be somewhat avoided by using a controller (since you can push the thumbstick forward a tiny amount to move slowly.Problem 2: What's even worse is that it feels like they increased the time that passes when you turn. In the old version you could do a quick 360 to get some situational awareness and plan your next move, even while being attacked. Now turning even 90 degrees is enough time for a guy to shoot you from halfway across the map it seems. Suspect a guy is behind you? Turning around is enough time for him to kill you, and ignoring him means he will kill you. Tough luck.The combination of these two changes (mistakes, honestly) ruins the flow of the game. It's more difficult, and while difficult does not = bad it also makes the game less fun, which IS bad. It feels like the only way to get a high score in the endless mode anymore is to hunker down somewhere where the enemies can only come at you from one direction and can't see you until they are close. That's right, they turned a game about acrobatics, style, strategy, and movement into a game about ...camping. Superhot was supposed to be DIFFERENT from normal shooters, and now it just feels more like them, and not in a good way.Let me show you what I mean:This first clip was captured by me before the changeshttps://killstagram.com/s/QuixoticSociableRazzmatazzIguanaThis second clip was also captured by me, on the exact same level, after the changeshttps://killstagram.com/s/OnlyCaringFernHorseSee the difference? Running around like in the first clip just isn't possible anymore, or is at least much more difficult to pull off. The amount of time it takes to do anything now, even simply looking around to understand what you're dealing with, is too much time.Now, I'm not gonna lie: That second clip was still pretty fun.And that's the thing. After all this, I still can't dislike this game. The 12+ hours I put into it before this patch got me more than my money's worth, and other than these two changes the game is unchanged.But it isn't as fun as it used to be.At the moment, I still recommend the game. The idea is fresh, the art fits perfectly, the story is great, the map designs are varied, the challenge modes change the game in neat ways, and the endless mode is a fun way to casually game while listening to a podcast. If you're a new player you probably won't even have any problems with the new changes since you don't know what it was like before.But for me, THE MOST INNOVATIVE SHOOTER I'VE PLAYED IN YEARS was the old Superhot, not this new one, and I hope they change it back.Edit: Additonal pre-patch footage of mine, again on the same level:https://killstagram.com/s/NeighboringExhaustedDeerKoalaUPDATE UPDATE: Most recent patch seems to have fixed the problems, game is great again. Hopefully it stays that way. I'm excited to see how the game will change in the future. Again- disregard what I said above, those problems no longer exist."
