76561198040492584,Not Recommended,322500,21505649,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,Flailmorpho,"Superhot is a game basically about trickshooting and making ""cinematic"" fights, you're going to find yourself doing things like shooting someone next to you, then because your next shot isn't up yet you throw the gun at the person shooting at you so they drop their gun so you can shoot them with their own gun, because that is surprisingly faster. And when it does it's job at making you feel cool it does it REALLY WELL.However, the game doesn't support it's instant death very well in terms of giving you enough information. Turning around to check your surroundings for people causes time to speed up and likely kill you in later levels where there's around 5 people attacking you at once, and there's no indicators other than where you're looking as to where enemies are going to be.Now dying isn't usually a problem in that many video games, but SUPERHOT is not your average video game, SUPERHOT thrives off of having flowing gameplay, and anything whatsoever breaking that flow turns it's incredibly fun gameplay into a quick slog of a game that you just want to get to the next level and really hate restarting over and over.One of the biggest problems is the assault rifle in the game. The Assault Rifle allows enemies to turn the game into a bullet hell that must be carefully navigated, instead of the early games ""do what you think is coolest"" gameplay the massive amounts of bullets makes you walk on eggshells trying not to be cool, but to just survive.In short: SUPERHOT turns from a game about being cool, into a game about being pixel perfect just to avoid dying, you will die over and over again trying to figure out just what the hell you are supposed to be doing and it stops being fun."
