,Not Recommended,322500,21879296,"Posted: 16 March, 2016",all,Loli Gagging,"The same review as the rest; this game is short. But more annoyingly, it's shallow. Since all enemies die in one hit, there's no point in skill shots. Since time moves when you do, there's no urgency in killing them, either. The katana is fun, I have to admit, but the rest of the time you'll just be frustrated at your inability to shoot anyone more than 10 feet away.At the end of the day, you fall into an incredibly dull routine of 'shoot guy, throw gun, grab gun, shoot guy', and the only time you'll die is when an enemy spawns in mere feet away and kills you because you weren't looking in that direction for all of a half a second.The bonus levels are just the main campaign, exactly, with some new rule, like 'only use katana' or 'only pistols', but the levels are exactly the same, featuring the exact same enemy spawn pattern. Being forced to use a specific weapon does very, very little to the gameplay- there wasn't variety to begin with; how is less helping? Do you really want to beat the same 25 levels OVER and OVER again with an even more limited arsenal? Even the endless levels are just copy-pasted from the main campaign."
