,Recommended,322500,22154340,"Posted: 30 March, 2016",all,Reist Windhunter,"PLZ READ THE ENTIRE REVIEW FIRST BEFORE JUMPING TO CONCLUSIONS: I DO NOT DESPISE THIS GAME IN ALL ITS ENTIRETY!!! :(Let me just say this: I do not see the fun or hype from this game...I have completed the demo, and played this game thoroughly enough. I am not hooked by the premise, and the game is truly just one big rage fest to me. Do I think it has an artistic form? Sure. Is it something dynamic or out of this world? Hell no, nothing that hasn't been done before in other games, just a bit differently. Do I think the mechanics are interesting? Sure...if you want to rage over a simple f*cking level that you end up spending almost an hour to beat...yeah. Me? I do not play games to get mad at them: I play them to have fun. This, although has its moments, has a lot of fixing to do, particularly throwing objects around corners.Overall, I rate this game 5/10...a -1 from a 6/10 only because the slow-time thing is not all that impressive, really...Its so dumb that the premise behind the game states that ""Time Moves When You Move"", and yet when I want to take a sec to analyze the scene, I am literally taken away from it because time does NOT move when I move, rather, time speeds up to NORMAL pace when you move...not stopping it completely...perhaps adding a new mode would fix this? A difficulty setting? Idk...it's thoroughly frustrating when I am let down from such a well-spoken title from other peeps who liked this game. All I see is a super-simplistic game lacking any real reason to make me play this again if all I do is get mad when I die everytime. Now, maybe if I take more time and play more, get the better ryhthm of the game, I may find a different opinion on the game, but for now: I am thoroughly unsatisfied that I spent 25 bucks on a game that makes me nothing but mad.On the bright side, I do like the implementation of a clever ""Killstagram"", and hope they add more features to the replay sections, such as replaying a level to try and make an even cooler clip, and playing with the timecode/timeline more, adding music, and so on...If they improve this mechanic, this will definitely make me want to play this more, and ignore all ragefests...even bump my rating up to a 8/10. But sadly for now, I can only give this a 5/10...its nothing too crazy, but definitely challenging to play, which is both inconsiderate to people new to FPSs, but smart to those who really want to have a blast and challenge back-to-back.Edit: After going back and playing through this all the way, and being patient, I found this game to be suprisingly addictive, and acceptionally challenging. Initially, I was frustrated beyond understanding with the mechanics, and some bugs, but once you understand fully how to engage the enemy, you can safely call this a simple, yet interesting shooter!I still think it has some improvements to make, but overall a solid game. Not really worth 25 dollars, IMO, but I am still content with my purchase.Also, something else to suggest: allow a sandbox/level creator! THIS WOULD INITIALIZE SO MUCH IMPROVEMENT, AND SO MUCH CREATIVITY, IT'D BE MIND-F*CKING-BLOWING TO THE FANS, MYSELF INCLUDED!!! :D"
