,Recommended,322500,21502183,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,The Leetelite,"SUPERHOT is a very interesting FPS with a very cool concept for gameplay and a nifty way of telling the story of the game.Unfortunately the story mode of the game is only about 2 hours long, which comes off as disapointing for some people, not for me since / Potential minor spoiler? / The gameplay gets constantly interupted by the narrative which while I found slightly entertaining I also found it rather obnoxious.Which meant that I could go on the play challence and endless mode which were a blast, in my opinon.Katana mode rocks socks.And yes, while the story mode being a mere 2 hours long the gameplay combined with challence mode and endless mode gives this a much higher potential amount of playtime.I heartily recommend it since I could get over how short the story was and enjoyed the gameplay enough to spent time in endless mode and challence mode, also the quality of those two hours ( which were completely awesome and badass ) was in my opinon worth the asking price, but I can definently see how the relatively high pricetag could put some people off buying it.So here is my recommendation to you in doubt : Buy it, check if the gameplay solely is something that would keep you entertained for a longer period of time. And if it is not then ask for a refund! This way you have atleast tried the game for yourself and can make a more solid standing point on how you see the issue.Keep in mind also that I got this game at the promotional sale at the price of about 20€ while the original price is a bit higher."
