,Recommended,322500,21508530,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,RolanDecoy,"I'm not much of an FPS player, but I really enjoyed this single player game.The story-line, in a nutshell, is about a software pirate whos life gets turned upside down after download something that at first glance seems to be a game. Playing this game, this...virtual environment... becomes more and more addictive.Like I said, this is a first person shooter, and it really is nothing more than that. But it focuses on that little nugget unlike any other game. Imagine a game where you are in a constant bullet time mode; Where the speed of the game is determined solely by you mouse moving or keyboard input. You are the one that decides the pace of the action, by combining melee and ranged combat, switching between the 2 in a split second.As much as this game looks and feels like an FPS, the strategy you employ and your ability to switch strategies whilst retaining your situational awareness will prove an interesting experience to say the least.If I had to compare this to other games, the ones that come to mind are Ronin, Max Payne and The Matrix, with a twist of The Stanley Parable.It looks good, although don't expect too much texture and model detail; It serves a purpose and it serves it well, and like most games that put mechanics ahead of graphical quality one shouldn't expect too much. I really love what they did with the menu system though ;-)There are some problems I have noticed in similar games though. For instance, you have the ability to throw an (empty) gun or melee weapon at your enemy to stagger or even kill them, but I found myself in situations where I saw my katana fly through my enemy without doing either, as if they didn't have a body (collision detection problems). In other situations my weapon would bounce off into some random direction, again without affecting them. Enemies firing their weapons AFTER you've punched it out of their hands, killing you by 'magically' spawning bullets out of thin air, weapons falling apart in mid-air because invisible wall (collision detection, once again).Nothing game-breaking, but annoying at times. The game is actually nicely split in small levels and that makes up more than enough from my perspective. This kind of fine collision detection, which seems to be the cause of the majority of these problems plagued Ronin as well and I'll take it as a symptom of the genre.All in all I highly recommend giving this addictive and unique shooter a try. Although, I must admit the price of 20 Euro's may be a bit steep for most."
76561198036608647,Recommended,322500,21511095,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,✌ The Dude™ ✌,"Very clever Idea, But over priced for 4 hours of gameplay.Seems they will sell alot of copies due to some clever advetising, So hopefully they will do the honest thing and give us a sequal/game thats worth £30 for £15 or be in the steam sale once a month whilst the price is high.Until then this game should be bought for £7.99"
,Recommended,322500,21522894,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,dennis12431,"Super Hot is a (currently) new Indie Game.The Main Goal of the Game is simple, clear the Level.But the twist is the Unique Mechanic the Game brings.""Time only moves, when you move"".The Game Executes the Mechanic pretty good.The only Problem i have is that the Guns (Espacilly the Pistol), feel very Slugish.That also makes it look like your just holding the weapon, instead of waiting for the recoil to wear off.At the End of each Stage you also see a replay in ""Normal speed"".I say that because, its basically just your Gameplay Speeded up which let it sometimes look weird.The Game is also REALLY short just about 2 hours of the ingame story,you can literally refund it.2 hours is kind of a joke, considering in the current state the game cost ~20€/$.So whats good and why should you buy it anyway?well first up:the game has alot of cool things.The most see able is the Death Physiks of the""Red Guys""They literally scatter like broken diamonds on the floor.Then because of the time only moves wh... yeah whatever you can do things like, catch a katana that you throw to yourself with the new mechanic. (Yes its really not just the demo that we all played a year ago).The new mechanic work like this:Every ~10 ingame seconds you can travel into the body of an enemy,with the side effect that,first: that enemy will drop their gun,second: the body you were in turns into an enemy.You will find yourself using that mechanic to get out of unavoidable situations or to travel to another part of the StageCONCLUSION:In the end the game is a very cool/very fun game to play,its just overpriced.Luckily its not just the demo we played already.MY SUGESTION:wait until the game gets a 50% sale.Considering theres nothing big to add into the game,this should soon happen.I hope i could help you."
