76561198154597510,Recommended,322500,31889324,Posted: 21 May,all,Juan Pablo,"Honestly, I cannot think of a game that I was more amazed by just by watching the trailer than I was when I saw this game's trailer; I had never seen anything remotely like this before and was instanly willing to pay the $25 for it. After downloading it, I instantly opened it and was astonished by how flawless the game is. Yes, there are probably some bugs here and there, but that's not the point. The story is so simple, yet so complex at the same time, and is assisted with amazing gameplay. The game's ""campaign"" isn't very long, one to three hours I would guess, but it is one the best I have ever played. While the game might seem repetative in some aspects, it manages to change how you approach your goal because you can't just run into a room with an assault rifle and mow every one down; the AI will shoot you before you can. Anyways, after you finish the story, you can play levels from the game and an endless mode, which is just endless waves of enemies (my record at the time of this post being writen is 90, which took forever to get). There are also tons of other parts of the game that I have not even touched yet, because there are so many of them. While people may say that this game is like a one-day thing, meaning that after a day you'll be bored of it, but I think that it is so much more than even a week of five hour sessions. My rating of the game is a 10/10; a masterpiece for a lack of better words."
