,Recommended,322500,21492209,"Posted: 26 February, 2016",all,Quelandoris,"Most Innovative Shooter I've played since the SUPERHOT Demo nearly 3 years ago.Pros:Gameplay is amazing, all the guns are highly responsive, levels are tightly and smartly designed (With the exception of the last part of the final level, which has a few too many blind corners)Slo-mo that actually makes you feel like Neo from the Matrix.There is a katana.There is a game mode for nothing but katanas.Interesting, if slightly underdeveloped plot and setting.Lovely spartan aesthetics.Metric Tons of replayability. There's something about this slo-mo gameplay that really lets you get creative with how you kill things.Mehs:Plot is PAINFULLY short, especially considering what an interesting cyberpunk world it creates. Its almost depressing that the devs did nothing with the setting aside for ""SAO VR Woaaaah""Visuals can get a little repetitive if you marathon the game for too long.There seems to be a lot of secrets in this game. Like A LOT A LOT. An ARG's worth, if I had to guess. I'm not great at that kind of stuff though, but it's something interesting to keep an eye on in the coming weeks.Cons:The game is SHORT. It only took me about 2 hours to beat the main campaign, and that's considering I was stuck on one level for around 30 minutes. This game is banking heavily off replay value to meet its $25 value. IMHO, it has more than enough additional content to merit the value, but if you're worried about it, get in on a deep sale, or ask a friend if they have a coupon (We all do.)Plot is a little meta. New gamers or people just not very into computers will likely not understand the themes of the plot.I'm willing to bet a lot of work went into the Secrets/ARG aspect of the game. Best to buy in quick if you want to be a part of that.Overall: IT LIVED UP TO 3 YEARS OF HYPE. 9/10. Great game, some flaws to be ironed out. If they make a sequel, and they adds some more mechanics and content to the sequel, SUPERHOT 2 could easily enter intothe best of the best for the puzzle genre."
