76561198047404421,Recommended,322500,21535663,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,Wollychop,"Ok.  Now here is a good game.  The big question people seem to ask is, is it worth the asking price?To me, yes.  If you are someone who gauges their dollar spent on games based upon hours, maybe not.  It cost me $20, but for me, there will be plenty of replayability here.  Maybe not for you -- it is completely subjective.The story is very ""meta"" and is of course short.  Now you do unlock modes.  But it might be worth waiting for a sale, if you think 20 bucks or so is too much to ask for your time.  I don't judge that and I understand it.However, I will say that I got a TON of enjoyment out of the ~2 hour story mode, and know that I can spend quite a bit of time in the unlimited mode.  You can play slow and methodical, taking advantage of the time stop, or try to go full on twitch FPS.  The very simple, but highly polished mechanics mean that you can get a lot out of each level.Do yourself a favor, if you really want to play this, avoid letsplays and twitches.I completely understand why some folks would not recommend this title at price.  No argument, that's a reasonable and subjective opinion.  I however think it is easily worth the asking price, especially given other games at that asking price.  I think I'll be able to pick this up a few times a week just to fart around and see different ways of completing levels.  That is TOTALLY DEPENDENT upon what kind of gamer you are.  If you want an epic, well written story for your dollar - no, stay away.  If you want something along the lines of THEY LIVE in a video game, that reminds you constantly you are playing a game, you might enjoy it.  And again, the mechanics are ROCK SOLID.If you like shooters, but also like turned based games where you can weigh your  options, this is an awesome little hybrid with some very cool mechanics.  It runs smooth.  If you want a 40+ hour adventure for your dollar, with a polished story, no, I'd say wait for a sale.  But overall I recommend it.I mean, the game makes you literally exit to windows and restart to continue the story, it is so ""meta"".  Contrived?  Sure.  But it adds to the immersion (whatever that really means).  It's a solid title.  I'd really like to see more from these guys,It's farily unique and might surprise you.  If you have any doubts, *wait for a sale*!!!  But otherwise, dive in."
