,Recommended,322500,21480282,"Posted: 26 February, 2016",all,Dirtyplatinum,"Its the most innovative shooter Ive seen in years.Now that we have that out of the way, lets actually get to it. SUPERHOT is a shooter/puzzle game. Its very short story tasks you with shooting red dudes. Its not a very interesting story, but they do with it what they can to make it an enjoyable hour and a half to 2 hours. The game is pretty stylish, and its simple look actually underplays how cool the action can be sometimes. The red dudes shatter in an almost glasslike way, making it pretty satifying to kill them in all sorts of ways.While that doesnt sound to interesting its the games ""puzzle"" elements that make it enjoyable. When you are not moving time moves at a snails pace. Giving you time to enjoy the mayhem around you. As glass shatters and bullets wiz by your head, you do a dance between machine gun fire to smack a dude in the face with a bat, before throwing it at another guy, and grabbing the machine gun from out of the air to riddle their friends with bullets.While the story is rather uninteresting and doesnt offer much replayability, it does have an Endless Mode and a Challenge Mode. These are honestly where you are going to spend most of your game time, with Endless Mode having several maps to hone your skills and even a type of challenge mode on those as well, tasking you with killing everyone in a timely fasion as one example. Challenge Mode will also take away some time while you plink away at the story mode with such things as Katanaonly Challange, which in my opinion is a standout among the other challenges.Other then the actually rather amazing ability to switch bodies with people there isnt much more to the game. But take it from me thats more then enough. I got through the story pretty fast, introducing me to the abilities I would need to master. And then I ran through the Katanaonly Challenge in about an hour, having already ran through the story. Now Endless Mode seems to be the thing for now.I completely recommend it, and think the $25 price tag is more then justifiable. Its has already given me 4-5 hours of enjoyment and can totally see Endless Mode sucking up quite a bit more time. Just dont expect the story mode to carry the game."
