76561197961215927,Recommended,322500,21579356,"Posted: 1 March, 2016",all,Myztkl©-Kev,"This game is the most innovative shooter I have played in years! Something was holding me back, but now im free.Definitely worth the $30 but,The story mode is underwhelming. It's a really cool concept and a good story but they could have easily dragged it on longer and still made a good story out of it, this must have been a time restraint because the only thing holding it back from being a 5 hour (at least) story is lack of more levels. My first play through took over 2 hours, I'd say roughly 2.5 hours which is comparable to portal 1 which suffered from most likely the same lack of maps with most likely a time restraint. Over-all I came out of it with a smile on my face.Graphics aren't anything next gen, but they are going for a dos era type game style (works hand in hand with the story delivery)Putting that aside, there seems to be a lot of replayability with challenge and endless mode. So far I've sunk close to 2 hours into endless mode and I was just about to go back in when I decided to update my review.Endless mode has 9 different maps with 4 different options to play on them including 2 kinds of time trials.Challenge mode I haven't tried yet but it basically speaks for itself. Most likely things like: ""get this many kills in this time"" or ""kill 6 enemies with less than 3 shots"" (these are completely fabrication used as an example as I don't actually know)a few things I would prefer would be to have a reminder pop up on the screen like the commentaries that you can body switch, because I always forget I can do that and removing the annoying ""Super Hot"" repeating message through your replays in story mode, once or twice would get the same point across but let you actually enjoy your replay (this is disabled in endless mode)The replay editor is very rudimentary but gets the job done, just annoys me that it has to play the entire replay in order to ""capture"" it so you can upload it.All in all great game, especially for people who like games where you challenge yourself to constantly beat your records in a slightly repetitive but extremely fashionable way. There's some good moments that end up happening when you just stop and go ""Oh s***, that crazy thing just happened!""TLDRPros:Good story delivered in a cool fresh wayCool new way to use time as the basis for a normally saturated shooter market that so far has me only want to return for moreLots of replayability with challenges and endless modereplay editor lets you show your friends how fancy you areCons:Short story modefairly bland graphics (was intended but could have a little more flash)menu delivery may confuse some people (again is all part of the era style)9/10 would shoot myself in the head again."
