,Recommended,322500,21722350,"Posted: 8 March, 2016",all,Löwenzahn,"Some games aren't made by their campaigns. This is one of them.SUPERHOT is made by its replayability. That explains the relatively short campaign, which actually suggests such replayability.All in all, it's a good game, and was worth my 2-3 years of wait. Not like I was ""OOOOOOOOOOOOMG SUPER HOT SUPER HOT,"" but I was waiting.There's still plenty to do after the campaign, with the ENDLESS Mode and the CHALLENGES, composed of several kinds with apparently 25 levels each, which gives you quite a lot of stuff to do.Gameplay is smooth. Only two detectable bugs, as of now:1-) Phantom walls, especially around corners of narrow obstacles;2-) Punching will occasionally result in an instant kill, especially if you face framerate drop at the moment of the punch.Summary:+Gameplay is what we expected: plan ahead, dodge, disarm, kill, etc., in the best bullet-time fashion.+Game is difficult, but fair. Expect occasional yelling.+Simplistic, almost-monochromatic graphics and absence of musical soundtrack fit the game perfectly.+After the campaign, gives you a series of challenges and an endless mode to keep the glass skull-cracking going.+Makes you feel pretty badass.+Well polished.+There's the Hotswitch resource that really adds umph.-Bullet collision can be somewhat disappointing, since a shotgun shell fragment can stop your 5.56mm round. Happens.-Very tiny bugs.-Short campaign that surely could use a continuing.?Low variety of weapons, but what more could we ask for? A crossbow? Shuriken? Oh, if we could actually use the electric drill instead of just throwing it.?Campaign is story-telling, not decision making.8.5/10"
