76561197995760735,Recommended,322500,21667841,"Posted: 6 March, 2016",all,ReSiDeNt_EviL,"I havent ever played a game quite like this before. It is like an FPS and a puzzle game that uses a pretty unique take on the bullet time mechanic that verterans of games such as Max Payne will fully appreciate.  It is amazing amounts of fun, it has a strange but compelling story mode and it is a bit of a mindfu$k but I loved it. Once you complete the main story various new gameplay modes, including an endless mode, open up that can keep you going for hours more.Let me try and explain why you should play this game whether you are a fan of FPS games or otherwise. This is a game where you can face 2 enemies at the same time, one firing an assualt rifle the other a double-barrelled shotgun. You see the bullets coming at you in super slo-mo. They are about 15 feet away and you are standing in a corridor with no exits and nowhere to hide while you have just a katana in your hands. You dodge their initial shots, turning to watch the individual bullets as they race slowly past you. You throw the katana in between the two of them body swap into the guy with the assault rifle, catch the katana in mid air and cut the other guy in half before he has time to point his shotgun at you. If you dont think that sounds like something you want to do. Then give this a miss. Otherwise buy it. I dont think you'll be disappointed."
