,Recommended,322500,21490588,"Posted: 26 February, 2016",all,The Killer Buddha,"SUPER! HOT! SUPER! HOT! You'll grow to love that sound.You start the game. A Red Dude is suddenly in front of you, fists balled, hand drawn back. You melee quickly, knocking him back and down. A quick look left shows an assault rifle on the table, but another Red Dude is coming through the doorway just across ther room with a drawn pistol. You judge the distance, and race for the AR. As the weapon comes to rest in your hands, you hear Red Dude fire a shot. You come to a stop and turn towards the oncoming bullet.Time suddenly slows to a crawl.You take careful aim, pull the trigger, and fire three precise shots. As time again begins to flow forward, your first bullet impacts the oncoming pistol bullet, casuing them both to shatter and deflect. The other two shells go flying into the chest and upper arm of the last Red Dude, causing him to crumple to the floor.SUPER! HOT! SUPER! HOT!Time only moves when you move. This unique mechanic transforms this unique shooting game into a problem solving strategy game which would be perfectly in place as a Matrix training scenario for Neo.The graphics are simple, but striking. The gameplay is addictive, the perfect combination of being easy to learn but difficult to master. The enemy.... Well, the enemy starts off oblivious, but they rapidly become aware of you. If there's not a Red Dude in front of you, he's probably sneaking up behind you.I think this one will easily be a cult classic."
