76561197968207989,Recommended,322500,21481113,"Posted: 26 February, 2016",all,Tersidre,"So I only have 117 minutes played of Superhot as of this writing. That was enough to get the game and play through the entire campaign and a couple of challenges.For what they are trying to do with this game its actually pretty neat, the whole puzzles with guns aspect is neat and a couple of the levels are really challenging. Having said that I was able to figure out how to beat all of them within a couple of tries. Really just basic trial and error techniques will get you there it doesn't require anything super intense to figure out where the enemies are spawning and which ones have which guns. The only level I felt I sort of squeaked by on was the melee one where you're in the cage. That one took about 5 or 6 tries for me to figure out who needed to die first and how to move to avoid them while still hitting them.Its not game of the year or anything and I really think the price tag is a little bit steep for what is offered here. About an hour and a half of a campaign maybe two or three hours if you're just not getting it. The value does come up some with the endless mode and challenges unlocked at the end of the campaign so thats sure to add some time onto the game for me.The whole replay sharing thing from killstagram is neat but I don't really see myself using it. I just uploaded one to get the achievement for doing it.If you're looking for a fun little game that has a bit of a unique twist on a first person shooter and don't mind some mild frustration while you learn to deal with situations that seem incredibly unfair (none of them really are its just a matter of understanding the way they want you to move) its a good game. I'd suggest waiting for a bit more of a steam sale, 20 bucks is a bit much id say when you see it down in the 10 dollar range or lower its worth it."
