,Recommended,322500,21733775,"Posted: 9 March, 2016",all,KillTheG1mp,"Superhot is what you would get if Portal, Hotline Miami and Max Payne were in an orgy and one of them got pregnant. It is  a FPS game, a puzzle game and a bullet ballet simulator. The developpers pour a lot of love into this game and it shows, drawing inspiration from the John Woo movies, the Matrix and many action flicks and games that came before it, distillating the very best of each into gaming perfection.Should you spend full price on this game? That depends on how you play games. Are you the type that rather plow quickly through a game and never touch it again? Or would you rather play endlessly and trying to beat your best time/score? If the latter is more down your alley, by all means, get this game ASAP. if, on the other end, you want a deep story that'll last long, look elsewhere, the story mode lasts for about an hour and a half and you then unlock endless mode (where you try to survive and kill as many red dudes as possible before eventually dying) and challenges, which recycles the main story levels and adds a twist to them, like only using the Katana or AD2013 mode where it's only guns + punches.All in all, if you're still unsure about the game, try to play it at a friend's if you can to make up your mind. For myself, this is the best 30$ (canadian) I spent on a game in a while!"
