,Recommended,322500,21585196,"Posted: 2 March, 2016",all,straechav,"The game is short. Very short. It'll take you about three hours to finish the very much meta story. That said, you can replay the levels (I'd call them ""scenarios"", they're too short to be called levels) and perfect your tactics or approach, you can also play endless mode where there is more and more enemies as time passes.The game plays a bit of a cross between puzzler and a shooter. You play in FPS (without gun at the start) and time moves only when you move, with those tools, you have to survive until the next level. It's all very stylized, abstract and mucho cool.It's short, and it's possibly a bit too pricey for the length it lasts. But honestly, it's just too great of a concept to be down about. It also has bazillion minigames, if you care about those, in the menu. Who gives a sh*t? I'm more in to the combat. It's pretty much flawless, and if they add more levels, or publish a DLC with more levels (hopefully more reasonably priced) I'll be all over it like a bad rash."
