,Recommended,322500,21638168,"Posted: 5 March, 2016",all,Jaree,"You know what, it takes time. Much like what this game is about (This is going to be a really indepth review for those actually considering purchasing this game, so hold on)At it's core, SUPERHOT wants you to believe it's a real game, not a short indie game. To be fair, it is essentially an indie game but there's so much more to it.What would you do if you had an innovative game mechanic and a great physics engine? You would create a game like SUPERHOT. The game, if you take aside all it's other mechanics, is basically an innovate shooter where time only moves when you move. It's straightforward and could make a great, CHEAP game (Unfortunately this game is a bit below compared to its price), but the devs made it much more. Here's how:- THE DIFFICULTY: Holy crap is this game hard! You will be frustrated within your first 30 minutes into this game! I almost refunded the game because of Level 5, but Googled a tutorial instead.- STORY: The story, is honestly one of the best I've seen in previous years. Without spoiling much, it had an innocent non-complex, arcady tone to it, but it becomes much more of a conspiracy as the game goes on... (Although do note that the story itself is only around 2 hours, but it unlocks some great modes once completed)- MECHANICS: It does get old eventually, but I love the innovative playstyle!Overall, if you're willing to spend a couple extra bucks, it's a great buy."
