,Recommended,322500,21537264,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,Fundz64,"SUPER.HOT.-A game where time only moves when you move.(@gamedevs: it's not the first FPS game to have this concept, but it is very well designed to be original of it's genre)This game's engine looks complex, but once you get the handle of the 'time handling' ability, the game couldn't get any easier to play it right through.  There are many 'thinking out of character' traits in this game, for the sake of advancing the storyline, but gameplay-wise, it is one of the most addictive singleplayer game i've played so far.Think 'Enter The Matrix' but actually a good game to play and where the glitches are actually supposed to happen.Their 'Killstagram' feature is very original- after completing a map, you can record a part of it, or the whole trip, and upload it on a real/fake social website for others to see- just keep in mind your username is not one you get to pick. It's a nice way to show off speedruns.  Though it is still under devellopment, It still has great potential.Though this game is expensive for it's short storyline (depending how good you are with strategic shooters) I would still recommend this to others if you finally want to have the authentic feeling of playing as 'the one' in the Matrix.SUPER.HOT.SUPER.HOT.SUPER.HOT.SUPER.HOT.SUPER.HOT."
