,Recommended,322500,21475137,"Posted: 26 February, 2016",all,Calcographer,"Not to spoil too much, I'll simply lay out the mechanics...Everytime you move, time advances. You'll see and be able to dodge bullets midflight. Weapons fly out of enemy hands (of which if you're close enough, you can grab), and an aesthetic that is incredibly unique. You'll be running, punching, jumping, throwing, and shooting. You'll create some rad combos, and then watch them occur in real time via the replay once the level is complete.Here's a couple tips:Mentioned previously, time advances when you advance. This includes ANY movement, even if you're just turning your head to look at an incoming projectile or to grab a weapon, time is moving. Albeit slowly with head turns and the like, but it is moving.Also, get familiar with each gun and how many shots are fired from each. You'll find yourself strategizing mid shootout when to throw your weapon into an enemy to continue your combo. Later in the game, most enemies have a weapon later in the game. Priortize! Nothing is more satisfying than chaining together a handful of actions moving from one enemy to the next, all while using their weapons against them.There is controversy regarding the length versus the price. I spent 4.6 hours on the main campaign. Don't be fooled by this. There is much more content in challenges, modes, and other various quirks in the ""computer"" you're operating, both during the main campaign, and post campaign.Either way, let me know what you think. I greatly enjoyed it, and applaud the devs on creating an awesome experience.Cheers."
