,Recommended,322500,21488988,"Posted: 26 February, 2016",all,Silvarren,"I don't often write reviews for games, but here I go. First, I love the slow-motion feature, particularly because time's not truly ""stopped"" when you're not moving.Second, I love the fact that there are a LOT of references to some obscure movies, like Oldboy. The game is, in large part, a number of different set pieces from various action movies that you play out in bullet-time. Is it fun? Oh yeah. So much fun. I love the feeling of satisfaction I get from solving the ""puzzle"" of how to move around the levels and in what order to kill the red dudes. I also love that you can cut bullets with a katana. And the fact that you can beat an entire level by throwing bottles at guys (it takes a while). Oh, also wanted to mention the fact that you can save your runs so that when you do pull off that perfect action movie combo, you can record it and put it up on Killstagram! :DYou might be questioning the price, but from what I've seen, they plan to be very active as developers, and release content in a lot of small packages, rather than just nickel-and-dime you with DLC every couple months. So, if you enjoy FPS and the ability to fight in slow motion,  I'd say the whole thing is definitely worth the money. I suppose one way to put it is... if you're in it to just beat a game, nah, you're better off waiting for a sale. But if you're wanting to be creative with your kills and gameplay, and want to be a part of something bigger than yourself, it's very worth it."
