76561198063618790,Recommended,322500,21507248,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,Kronzo,"This game's main story maybe only about 2 hours or so long, but it is worth it beyond your wildest dreams! Let's get this out of the way first: the pricing is a little steep. If this game went of about £10 or so, it would be just right, but even so, the game is utterly brilliant and beautiful that you probably won't care. SUPERHOT's main game mechanic allows you to control time; in a sense. There is no button to pause it or anything like that, but it's only when you move that time does as well. This allows for amazing crazy fights, plus all of the combined fighting equipment, ranging from pistols and shotguns, to crowbars and bats; even everyday obejcts like TVs, pool balls and power drills. Of course, there had to be a katana, which you can slice bullets in half with by the way.The game's plot and overall story is short but sweet. After you have taken the couple of hours to complete it, endless levels and challenges are unlocked, which are the best part of SUPERHOT. There are lots of different main menu easter eggs and extras that are somewhat fun to browse through. but they are merely a distraction.If you want it in simple terms, here:Pros:-Beautiful game in both gameplay and art design-Original and awesome game mechanics-Addicting and exhiliratingCons:-Somewhat steep on pricing for what's in the game so it is recommended you get it on sale if you are unsure about itOverall, brilliant and magical; a strange homage to Martix styled fighting and Quentin Tarantino paced action."
