76561198119187991,Recommended,322500,23742957,"Posted: 23 June, 2016",all,GallowsHumor,"So I got this game on the Steam Summer Sale and I have to say it was definetly worth the purchase in my opinion. The campaign is about 2-3 hours long depending on how good you are, and a lot of that time will be spent trying to finish the last level which was almost as painful as some of the flooding missions in Ori: The Blind Forest. Anyways, the story was really interesting and good, but this game isn't supposed to be something you are interested in for the campaign, it's the concept and the many modes that come after beating the story that set it apart. So the basic concept is time pratically stands still until you start moving. Tiny movements (such as turning your head) speed time up slightly while big movements (such as walking) speed time up to regular speed. I would honestly say this is almost more puzzle than FPS similarly to how some stealth games are more puzzler than it is an FPS or third person shooter. This game has tons of replayablitity because there are a ton of modes/challenges that you can unlock after finishing the story.I would have to say this is definetly one of the most innovative shooters I've played in years! super fun and highly reccommend if you are looking for a ""dumb fun"" type game with a little bit of a puzzle twist.I do have some complaints 1) sometimes it's hard to tell where you get hit from, or wheather or not something should have hit you which can be annoying. and 2) I saw a shotgun blast go through a pillard and then kill me a couple times on the last level (unfortunatly I didn't get time to screenshot it before I died). Lastly I know some people are mad that it is Oculus exculsive and I get that but I'm not interested in getting VR anytime soon so it doesn't bother me in any way and I'd still reccommend it."
