,Not Recommended,322500,22092487,"Posted: 27 March, 2016",all,Besipeitl,"Well, SUPERHOT is out for a while now and now i am writing a little Review.First of all, i didn´t backed SUPERHOT on Kickstarter or so, but i saw the Footage there and the whole campaign itself, and i have to say, the game is lacking a lot of features they promised, like the grenades and stuff and the visuals looked a LOT better in the Kickstarter Video. So as a backer i would feel a bit betrayed after i gave so much money for this project only to see, that a lot of things that were promised are not there.Next Point is, that the game is SUPERSHORT. The main story is made out of 26 level or so. And the level are short, really short. I finished the main story, which i won´t spoiler here, in about 112 Minutes.After the main story there isn´t much to do. There are 9 arena maps or so and some challanges, where you have to complete the main story with some different conditions, and 2 mingames. So there isn´t much to do.Also the game is getting boring after a short amount of time because the whole game is made out of ONE game mechanic, not more. ""Time moves only when you move."" That is the only feature that the developers could create in two years. And the idea of this mechanic is really cool, and i liked it, but you can´t build a game out of one mechanic, which is getting boring after 90 minutes.On Top of that, the story i mentioned earlier is a short and meaningless story, of a guy who is playing SUPERHOT.At least there is a Replay feature. But this feature is a mess and hard to use. it takes a huge amount of time to record your run. Maybe im just stupid, but it took me about 15 minutes to figure out, how to upload my replays to this weird SUPERHOT Instagramm Rip-off.And here a nice hint for the developers. Don´t use a white Color for the letters, when the whole background of the game, basically the whole game is white too.So, my final statement is, i would not recommend this game for this price. 22 Euros is way too much for this short and tiny game. The things, that are there are cool, but there are so many things missing, like a level editor, which is necessary for a game with only 26 level, better graphics, more level, more game mechanics. In my opinion the game is not worth its 22 Euros, 5 to 7 Euros would be a much better price.After the first short demo and two years of developement, the developers came out with this unfinished game. It is a shame, that people backed so much, and got ""betrayed"".I could have easily get a refund for this game after its main story, cause it is so short, but i didn´t because the game has potential. I really hope, that the developers will step up and update this game with a level ediot, maybe a graphics update, or maybe they will add more level by themselves, but in this state i would not recommend this game"
