76561198119593083,Recommended,322500,21518101,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,Railang,"To start off I would like to say I recomend this game fully to anyone and everyone who enjoys a game that pushes their limits to be unique. Sometimes it works, other times it doesn't. SUPERHOT nailed it.The game overall is based around its gameplay, and more specifically its gameplay mechanics. Time only moves when you move. You use this to your advantage to plan out the fight and make intricate dodges or shots. Honestly this mechanic IS the game, so if you're looking for groundbreaking multiplayer experiance or story you're not going to be satisfyed with SUPERHOT.That being said, I think most every game should get this game as it is unique and very enjoyable. I can already tell I will be spending many hours on this game trying to get perfect runs, testing my limits and challenging myself. It has amazing replayablity and is well worth the price.Overall Rating 8/10Story - 4/10As I said before this game was not based off of story. However it does have some inside of it that drew me in to some degree. It kept things mildly intresting though it wasn't what made me keep booting up the game after leaving for work in the morning.Game play - 9/10I am really hesitant to give this game a full 10 for its gameplay. The only two things that are holding it back is two very small things that most probably don't care about. This game has no ability to run, keeping your movement at a crawl when you are trying to move around a map. Most of the time this plays into your favor, other times it can be a slight annoyance. The other thing is the inability to crouch, which would give you the ability to dodge more attacks and help with the overall game in my oppion. Either way the gameplay of SUPERHOT is phenominal and the mechaincs of it are amazing. Like i said before, this game is built around its gameplay.Replayability - 8/10This game will pull you back to it undoubtably. You feel like a badass and want to get that run perfect and feel a sense of satisfaction when you do. I personally found myself up much later than I usually am just becasuse I was so engrossed in the game. The next day at work it was on my mine frequently and I found myself booting it up as soon as I got home.Style - 9/10I am weird and judge a game highly by how it looks. If something is ugly I am not going to spend more than a few minutes looking at it, and thats only if it's an intresting ugly. Superhot is a minimalistic art style that plays extreamly well into its gameplay and its performance. I would be suprised to find a computer that couldn't run this and have it look good. The game's art style is simple, yet functional and elegant.Depth - ?/10Unfortunatly I cannot say as to how deep this game will go with its progression system. While it is already very good and offers quite a few rewards for completeing certian challenges or getting so far in endless ect. There has been hints are more to come. Right now I would give it a 6/10 just because it seems like there is only small modifications to gameplay and new maps. However there is no really unique enemies or weapons to experiment with, which isn't terrible, thoguh it would add another layer to the game to make it more intresting.Anyways those are my thoghts on SUPERHOT. I would recomend this game to anyone in a heartbeat, so if you're still reading this review, scroll up, click add to cart, and buy the game already!"
