,Recommended,322500,21510792,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,SickWheelchairCombos,"First off, absolutely baseline recommended. Game is fun as hell. Pricetag vs content wise, there are 33ish levels, each of which is pretty damn good. Each level is playable in both an initial story mode, and a series of pretty consistently entertaining challenge modes. One of the challenge modes forces you to play through the whole game with only a katana. The katana can cut bullets in half. There's also a speedrun mode, for people who like that kind of thing. If you've played the demo and absolutely loved it, or you thought ""This was fun, but it needs the ability to cut through enemy bullets as you dodge and weave toward them and cut their head off,"" this is probably worth the money. If you've played the demo and you don't immediately feel the need to own the full thing, wait for a sale. If you haven't, check out killstagram dot com for a bunch of gifs of the game, and superhot dot com to play the demo.The most innovative shooter I've played in years."
