,Recommended,322500,21530417,"Posted: 28 February, 2016",all,Mayo,"I've been following SUPERHOT for a while now. Played the demo countless times.While I applaud the developers for their innovative ideas in gameplay and the fact that the game was released as a completed title I have mixed feelings for recommending this title. My original post was going to be a NO but I changed it at the last minute. So, this YES review will likely read as a NO.The largest overwhelming issue is the length of the game. Not only is the whole game easily beaten in a single two or three hour sitting but the levels themselves are small and short. You spend as much time in the menus and 'cut scenes' as you do fighting. Some of the beginning levels are so basic and short that they take less than a minute to finish.Difficulty was also a bit of a let down. Unlimited mode gets a bit more exciting but the story itself (which you have to finish to get unlimited mode) was extremely easy for me.While some may like the visual aesthetics I can't help but wonder what this game would have been like with a graphical overall. This is minor as the game did not pretend to be something it wasn't, but I can't help but feel a little frustrated that I built a powerful gaming PC to play 'indie' titles. Again, this is more of a personal complaint though.Speaking of difficulty and personal complaints, I really disliked the 'hot switching' function in the game. This single handedly made the game insanely easy for me. So much so I just decided not to use it. I understand it's reasoning within the game's story but I just wasn't a huge fan of it.Lastly, the biggest reason I can't suggest this game, is the price. At nearly $25 (or $22.49 as of right now) it's just not meaty enough. The levels are short. The mechanics are amazing, but simple and not really explored much throughout the game.However, after typing all of this up and thinking of the experience I had and that fact I've been playing it on and off as a quick fun game on breaks and inbetween work, I have to say I enjoy it quite a bit. Yes, it's kind of shallow in a lot of ways, and it's probably not worth the money for the amount of content it has in it, but I would recommend people at least look into it. So, I'm going to go back to the beginning and change it from a NO to a YES."
