,Recommended,322500,21555842,"Posted: 29 February, 2016",all,Ebeta2,"IT'S THE MOST INNOVATIVE SHOOTER I HAVE PLAYED IN YEARS. SUPERHOT. SUPERHOT. SUPER HOT.Joking aside, SUPERHOT has a really cool mechanic allowing time to flow only when you move, making this unlike traditional FPS games. It's great because anyone can play this with ease, and is especially nice for first-time FPS players. It's more of a strategy game in the fact that instead of just running around just killing red dudes, you have to analyze the environment to see what you can do to beat the levels. The best thing about this is: you (almost) have all the time in the world to figure this plan out. Watch where they run, what weapons they're using, and dodge the bullets flying past you. Plan the assult as you go.Other than that, the visual and art style is amazing, and it's so satisfying to see the replay of what you did in real time once you complete a level. You feel like neo from the matrix, or the most badass soldier ever. To top it all of, it has a computer sim aspect to it (which is a personal favorite theme of mine when it come to games), which really emphasizes the techicality of the gameplay and the story plot.If you're looking for a shooter that is basic, easy, and feels so satisfying to play, this is your game.SUPERHOT. SUPERHOT. SUPERHOT."
