,Recommended,322500,28705801,"Posted: 27 December, 2016",all,wildgoosespeeder,"It's the most innovative shooter I've played in years.Without using the words it wants me to say at the end of the campaign:I am not at all interested in the games typically associated with and other games trying to be those games in the FPS genre (CoD, Battlefield, etc.), at least until I played this game. I really like the concept of time moving at regular speed only when you move. Turning yourself around makes time flow a little bit while idling makes time move probably at Unity Engine's slowest rate. This is a slow strategic shooter, not a fast-paced on-your-toes shooter.There is a frustration factor because you can die with just one hit, but it mostly tolerable because the levels are short enough where that won't be the case for long after some practice. For low end machines, this game could become quickly unplayable. I have a guide that should explain better:http://www.steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails?id=824619568The campaign is pretty short, but most of your fun will come from trying the endless and challenge modes. This is where the mechanics really get interesting because this is where you can try some insane maneuvers and rack up some kills.The only thing that can make this game better is maybe a rewind feature. Can't have it all the time so maybe like the ""switch bodies"" mechanic, have similar limitations.Overall, definitely recommend, although the game is a bit too pricy for what it has to offer."
