76561197960411207,Recommended,322500,21503686,"Posted: 27 February, 2016",all,Cral,"Changing my review because I was a little hasty initially.The story mode is very short and the interruptions from the narrative are more than a little annoying, but the game really comes into it's own with the challenges and endless modes. Challenges cut away a lot of the fluff of the story mode and focus entirely on gameplay, with each challenge requiring you to follow a set of forced rules (katana only or one bullet per gun) and are really fun. Endless mode is basically survival and can be a lot of fun when stringing together 5 or 6 kills in a few seconds.It still feels like the movement and animation are unfinished, and I've come undone thanks to a few infrequent bugs (thrown items passing through enemies, sword range changing from swing to swing) but those issues are rare and I've enjoyed most of the time I've spent with the game."
