,Recommended,322500,22086836,"Posted: 27 March, 2016",all,Dominix99,"SUPERHOT is unlike any FPS you've ever seen. This is one of the most innovative shooters of our time and I was overjoyed when I saw that it had finally made it to steam. I had played the early online version of this game many years ago when it was just an idea, and was blown away at the concept. The premise of the game is that you have to kill a bunch of red dudes through a variety of different settings in a world where time only moves when you do. This makes for some seriously epic and fun slow-motion gameplay. You may not think there would be a story to this game, but there is, and it's a creepy one at that. (The ending is also fantastic) The art style is also something to note here: the red glass-like bad guys on top of the simplistic white background makes this game feel like a work of art. (which it is) The sound is amazing and the graphics are great. You can tell that the developers really care about this game and it shows. You also unlock a bunch of new content after completing the main story. I'm extremely satisfied with this game and it's definitely something you should try for yourself."
