,Recommended,322500,21831163,"Posted: 14 March, 2016",all,Chuckle Butt,"SUPERHOT is essentially a first-person shooter in which you combat faceless, nude men who are made entirely out of glass and Hot Cheetos and live in a digital dimension in the sky where all non-static objects are white and all static objects are black and made of glass. The unique bullet-time mechanic only allows time to flow when you move your character. Weapons include pistols, shotguns, and rifles with finite ammo which can be thrown to stun an enemy as well as baseball bats and katanas. The katana is by far the most powerful weapon because it can kill an enemy with one hit and it doesn't break, even when thrown. You can also use random objects in the game as melee and/or thrown weapons. Following a fairly short story mode, you can unlock Endless Mode and Challenge Mode which offer several levels of addtional content. But yeah, for the most part, you're just going to be killing some Red Guys. This game is a very refreshing, challenging, unique, and innovative shooter that also offers room for strategy, a good buy for it's full price but if you don't want to splurge, you should definitely get it when it's on sale if you're interested."
,Recommended,322500,21826157,"Posted: 13 March, 2016",all,WafflezLord,SUPERHOT IS THE MOST INNOVATIVE SHOOTER I'VE PLAYED IN YEARS!
,Recommended,322500,21820977,"Posted: 13 March, 2016",all,JJC1138,"This is right up my alley. The 'time only moves when you move' mechanic works brilliantly. I like the short, easy-to-replay levels, so you can experiment and improve your skills without risking having to replay very much. I like the short story mode so you can easily complete it in a day or two (and there are challenges left afterwards if you want to play more). The progression and learning-curve are great. There's even a well-done clever narrative. All around superb!"
