,Recommended,322500,21817275,"Posted: 13 March, 2016",all,myHaggis,"Superhot is a very innovative shooter, with a new mechanic that no other game [to my knowledge] has tackled before. The twist to it, is that time only moves when you move. If you are standing completely still, time will move at an extremely slow pace. Turn your head, and time will move at half speed. Walk or jump, and time moves at full speed. You may think that this would make the game much too easy, however you are always outnumbered, and a single shot or punch kills you. That's right, no health bars, no health pack, just one life. The game itself is fantastic, runs smoothly, and has a neat art style, which makes its con all the more painful. It only has two hours of content. You could stretch it to three, but you would have to play slowly. I am almost finished with my second playthrough, and only 5 hours was put into it. My reccomendation, is to put it on your wishlist, and wait for a sale, but for now, it just can't justify its 25 dollar price tag."
