76561197979487649,Recommended,322500,22047015,"Posted: 25 March, 2016",all,Trashware,"People who can only get two hours of fun out of this game apparently don't seem to get it, which is a shame. As much as I agree and also would have liked to see more levels in Story Mode a level editor seems like a much more needed addition to this game. The story introduces the most innovative shooter mechanics you will have ever seen in years in a (close to becoming stale) fourth-wall-braking-Unity-engine-kind of way rather than really trying to tell a story. But unlocking, mastering and completing the additional challenges is what it really seems to be about, if you actually care to open those folders and click on them. Do that and it will keep you occupied for at least 15-20 or more hours and to me that's perfectly worth the full price.Nevertheless this game does feel somewhat incomplete because of the lack of a level editor, preferably with a Steam Workshop page as well. With the way the story is told, game aesthetics like folder structure, fake chat-implementation etc the game implies a degree of connection to community and user-creativity that remains unfulfilled right now. Implement such a feature and there's enough meat (and veggies) on the menu for everyone, probably."
