,Recommended,322500,22370623,"Posted: 11 April, 2016",all,jkangas77,"SUPERHOT is by all means an utterly superb game. You can slice bullets out of the air, people! However, I'm assuming everyone already knows this, so instead in this review I am going to address the price point.For a game that costs a quarter of $100, many people are complaining about how it has way too short of a story to justify its price. Now, it is entirely true that the story is short (it took me ~3 hours to complete and that's mainlly because I'm kinda bad at shooters in general), but the story was quite unique though quite frankly the story is not the reason you should buy this game. This game is about slicing red dudes in slow motion, not about spending hours on some sort of plot!For $25 you get:- A 2+ hour story mode- 15+ endless arenas (which you unlock after story)- 8+ challenge modes which let you replay the story in a UNIQUE way (I've unlocked the first few and they reall change things up)- Incredibly fun and unique gameplay- Basic replay editor- Speedrun modesIn all, this is a great game to pick up and play, especially if you're a completionist, and is totally worth $25 if you're looking for a game that is simply entertaining and highly replayable. 'Nuff said.Well, I also forgot to mention that...... It's the most innovative shooter I've played in years ;)"
