,Recommended,322500,22716137,"Posted: 29 April, 2016",all,Jakey-Poo,"SUPERHOT has to be by far my most anticipated game, and for the most part, it delivered. Story wise, the game is short, but for the completionist inside of you (or if you want the game just because of the cool time mechanic), you may be looking at quite a few hours of gameplay. The Challenge, Endless, and Arena Modes are unlocked once you finish the story.There is one thing that bugs me about some of the negative reviews, to the point where I have to say something. You may have read from them that the game is pretentious, saying that at the end it wants you to ""spam your friends about the game."" At the end of the game, yes, they do want you to do that, but if you pay attention to what's happening in the story, you'd understand why. It's not so much that it's pretentious, it's just a finale to the story. If you did pay attention to the story and still don't understand what's happening, then read this MAJOR SPOILER:When your computer crashes because your character's system got nuked or whatever which is what happens after you kill yourself(?), the system starts to take over your mind. This is what's happening when the screen flashes ""MIND IS SOFTWARE"" and ""THE SYSTEM WILL SET YOU FREE."" When your character's mind has been completely taken over and uploaded to the system, the system then instructs you to spread the game in order to upload more minds to the system.Overall, a great game, if a bit on the pricey side. Plus, VR support soon. So that'll be awesome."
,Recommended,322500,22719726,"Posted: 30 April, 2016",all,Ryno,"SUPERHOT is a first-person shooter with a unique twist, time in the game only moves when you move around as the player. So if an enemy shoots at you, you can move out of the way to shoot them. It emphasizes thinking out your plan of attack instead of rushing in guns blazing. After completing a level in slow-motion you'll get to see your actions play out at normal speed.Pros:+The game has a unique mechanic that works really well+The aesthetics of the game are minimal, but they work really well+The main campaign is short and sweet, and you unlock 2 new modes for beating the game.+ The new modes you unlock allow you to explore the mechanics more and challenge yourself with different limitations (including limiting what weapon you can use or forcing you to beat the game w/o dying)+The levels are short and when you die you can retry them almost immediatelyCons:-If you don't care for challenge modes, the main game is only 2 hours long.-Cheap deaths resulting from enemies that pop out of nowhere with no way to prepare against them-The game costs 25$ for a 2 hour campaign and 2 challenge modes, which is WAY overpriced-The story is pretenious, and the theme has been overdone in the past several years.Nitpicks:=The game repeats the phrase SUPERHOT like a million times and I wanted to shoot myself near the endI'd wait for the game to go on sale for about 15$ and then pick it up, the core mechanics are solid enough to warrant trying it out and it's unique."
