76561198064590301,Recommended,322500,26227540,"Posted: 26 October, 2016",all,AllGlorytoHypnotoad,"Ok folks, here's the deal. If its on sale, go for it. If you pay $30, you are going to be disappointed. Most of the bad reviews I've read seem to be from a position of overpriced instead of not being fun. I love it.First of all, time never stands still (except in one challenge mode.) Time always churns at a snail pace and the more character movement you have, the more time speeds up to normal. So when you move your mouse around, you are moving and time does speed up. Some people call this a super annoying flaw. We call those people ♥♥♥♥♥ gamers. But before I digress...There are no graphics to speak of. The lackluster screenshots do it accurate justice. It is not a beautiful game by any stretch. For what the game is, however, they work. The stark contrasts and geometric simplicity are kind of refreshing when many games over-saturate backgrounds. It started as a design constraint and turned into a legitamate style.The gameplay is hectic. And loads of fun. I will say there exist ways to exploit the AI, which I have used to my advantage more than once. You hide behind a corner and run into the wall until someone comes. Then you clober them.There really isnt a story to the game. Something about a hacker game that sucks people into the computer and turns them into hitmen or something. I dunno. You really don't need it though. The main 'campaign' doesn't take exceptionally long to beat, but it does unlock endless mode. And at heart this is an arcade style game.Once I stopped trying to ""win,"" I began to have massive amounts of fun just trying to pull off ridiculous feats and failing over and over and over (there are no load times btw.) Its when you pull off a brutal combo thats fluid and technically magnificent, you can get a lot of satisfaction seeing it replayed at regular time.Pros-Insanely fun-No load times-Lots of replayability-You can cut bullets with a swordCons-If you pay more than $15 you are overpaying.-No modability in a platform that begs for it.-""Graphics suck"" if thats your position on things. (Trying to be unbiased here)Bottom Line: 6/10If the regular price were $15 bucks I would bump it up to a seven. Its loads of fun, but I would like to see more done with it before it deserves a higher score."
