,Recommended,322500,26448854,"Posted: 5 November, 2016",all,Dr. Cyanide Ph.D,"Though it has a relatively short campaign, and simplistic gameplay, SUPERHOT is built on one feature that is absolutely refreshing in the FPS genre that is dominated by military shooters: TIME STOPS WHEN YOU STOP.Though it sounds overpowered in a way, the game presents the challenges to you in a way where you need to actually stop and think of your next action before moving. You might feel like a god at first, but as the missions progress, you'll start feeling as a fragile as tissue paper, and will need to carefully calcuate your next move. The missions allow the time-stop feature to be shown in its full glory, and I'd love to see more updates to this game (or even a sequel) that shows more.Story wise - Meh. Its okay. Something something mind control, dog, no choice, computers, etc etc.I'd recommend this game, ESPECIALLY if it is on sale. It'll give you a few hours of entertainment, and you might even start it back up a few more times just for a few missions."
