76561198102780380,Recommended,322500,30892411,Posted: 1 April,all,ACK,SUPERHOT SUPERHOT SUPERHOT SUPERHOT SUPERHOT SUPERHOT the most inovative shooter ive ever played!8/10
,Recommended,322500,25999973,"Posted: 12 October, 2016",all,Blackhat,"I played the free flash version of Superhot before it was a real game. Just that small taste seared the extreme amounts of potential into my head, and the mind-blowing opprotunities of the mechanics.And the full game delivers. The few glitches from the free version have been polished out, and the white with bright red astetic gives the game a clean and professional look. The brilliant mechanic, in which time slows down and speeds up relative to the players movement speed, is used to the fullest, and combined with the 1 shot 1 kill, the game makes gun battles tense and exciting, while offering a playstyle geared towards planning and thoughtful placement. The sound design is very well done, and the levels are quite varied, giving a health amount of variety in terrain.As good as this game was, I still have a few quarrels with it. The campaign is very short, and took me around 3 hours, knocking it out in an afternoon. I also feel that ammo counters on the weapons would have been a good idea. You also get an ability later on which allows you to possess an enemy, and a recharge meter or bar would have been very useful. While the level are varied, the enemies are not. Yes, they will ocassionally use different weapons, but they are all red, crystaline mannequins at the end of it all. I hoped for enemies with say, different body types, or sepcial weaknesses, or specialized abilities. The same goes for the weapons. You have a pistol, a shotgun, and a burst fire assault rifle. You also have some melee weapons, and a katana. The throwables are all basically reskins of one object, and I feel that more variety would have helped. Possibly a sniper rifle, or a minigun of some sort, or just more types of weapons. The player character feels quite bulky at times, as bullets you were sure missed still manage to hit you, making the player feel like they're wearing a cardboard box. When you finish a level,The plot is quite interesting, being about virtual reality and the like, but I felt that they designed the game, then bashed the plot about with a hammer until it fit together, which I feel is the wrong way to do things. I feel that the plot should be written, then events connected with levels and fights.When a level is completed, a video plays of you doing the level in real time, which would have been great, but the video is obscured by the phrase, ""Super...Hot!"" flashing infront of the clip.After the campaign is finished, endless modes and challenge levels, which is the campaign with a certain twist added, or removed, are added.I must say that I quite recocmend Superhot, it's great bloody fun, and it really breaks up the monatany of the twatting about in modern war shooters. It's wonderful, has a few issues, but it's very worth it, and is still great.Highly reccomend"
