76561198093268728,Recommended,322500,26295409,"Posted: 29 October, 2016",all,pendulum,"I throughly enjoyed this game. For me, it goes beyond the gimmicky feel I expected characteristic of games emphasizing a single unique play mechanic. I found the story, while skimpy on details, thought-provoking and unique. It left me musing on the nature of self and filling in the blanks as to what I actually whitnessed in the story.However, this strength neighbors its shortcomings. Even at $15 when I bought it on sale, the game leaves me wanting more for its asking price. There is just one enemy type. About four distinct weapons. It took me about three hours to play the story mode. It's a good game, but I don't feel that it belongs at its asking price even discounted to $15! In my opinion, I would value it at about $8-$10 worth of game. $15 is a bit steep. $25 is just too much.The game didn't launch on my Mac through Steam on the Halloween update. I had to use Show Package Contents on the actual game app file and run the executable in the terminal. The game stutters at Fast settings on my very capable graphics card. A little better testing for performance on multiple platforms would have been nice.I greatly enjoyed this unique game, but I feel that the game lacks content for its price point at the time of writing. The authors have indicated that they will be releasing a free DLC in the future. If and when they do, the game could become a better deal overall."
