,Recommended,322500,31404810,Posted: 27 April,all,Melovinci,"SUPERHOT... SUPERHOT... SUPERHOT... SUPERHOT...You will hear this phrase approximately 400 times while playing SUPERHOT. You are a player in a first-person shooter (yes, that was meant to be meta) where time only moves when you move. You play the game at a speed somewhere between real-time and a complete stop. You are moved through a series of scenarios where the goal is to kill all the red guys. The way time moves means you are able to dodge bullets, line up shots and quickly asses the situation without getting riddled with bullets. It only takes one bullet to kill you, in the same way it only takes one bullet to kill the red guys. If you die, you start again.SUPERHOT does try and add some uncessary Matrix-esque metagame to what is a fun shooter experience, and this could be considered appropriate given the bullet-time theme of the game. I wouldn't rate the metagame very highly, or not at least its delivery.The reason why you play this game is for the ""replay"", the result of a successful run, played back to you in real-time.  Which means a 30 second replay is the culmination of about ten minutes of gameplay. This replay is somewhat marred by the words ""SUPERHOT"" flashing across the screen while being chanted with computerised montony, but is still satisfying to watch.SUPERHOT does let you pull off some incredibly fun, action-movie style fight scenes. Like jumping over an incoming car in a car garage; punching someone, causing them to let go of their gun; grabbing their gun and shooting them in the head; doing a quick 360 spin around to take out a read guy approaching from behind; running forward towards two more red guys, weaving between bullets; shooting one of them, throwing your empty gun at the other; punching the guy who just appeared out of nowhere from between two parked cars; grabbing the gun from the man who received your old gun to the chest; shooting the out-of-nowhere man; and then- ah♥♥♥♥♥♥ just took a katana to the chest... start again.SUPERHOT is a lot of fun and an interesting and unique concept for a game. It does come with some associated fluff that sometimes accompanies indie games, but is ignored easily enough for the experience."
