,Recommended,322500,30231075,Posted: 27 February,all,Mλgnetism,"It's like the demo with expanded levels and concepts, which is completely excellent. No complaints gameplay wise. The style ranges from sterile enclosed environments with great ambiance which sometimes almost feels like a surreal crime movie, which I think is pretty cool and an interface based off of old computers with slightly annoying transitions and choices.The story starts off intriguing at first and you're genuinely interested in it, but it tries to impress you with fourth-wall breaks and aggressive story telling which consists of nothing but ackamarackus. Even though the story was advertised to not be in your face, (similar to Half-Life's environmental story telling), it ironically became too overbearing and annoying.Unfortuanetely, the game's length still seems short and ends suddenly, which is a shame because the gameplay is worth going through the bad story. But, it is better to have a short competent game than a bloated, messy game of many hours. There are challenges to extend replay value which are fine like using katanas only, but for the length, the asking price is too high.Get it while its low in price. $10 or lower seems reasonable to me."
