76561198145160690,Recommended,322500,33905997,Posted: 30 July,all,VirtualOwl14,"Superhot is an FPS game that revolves around the concept of time moving when you do, and is good fun. You are tossed into one of many arenas in the game that resemble the real world, with monochrome visuals. Your only enemies are red characters weilding 1 of 4 weapons, a machine gun, shotgun, pistol, and sword. Each takes one hit to kill. It becomes somewhat puzzle like at times, as you have to prioritize your enemies, and know how to use the time mechanic to your advantage. Another mechanic is hot-switching, which lets you take the spot of enemies while disposing of your body, though it does have a cooldown. The story, while found pretentious by some, is pretty okay. It's relatively simple and doesn't get in the way of the game TOO much. My only gripes with the game is that it's relatively short, and somewhat unforgiving at times. I reccomend this game, however, not for the price it's at. Get this game on sale."
76561198170141333,Not Recommended,322500,30744219,Posted: 25 March,all,kimmy2668,"The physics and the general gameplay is amazing, not to mention the amazing feeling you get from stabbing a guy, taking his gun and shooting his friend with it, but after a while the game gets tedious, repetative, and slow. I know it's $25 for a 2 hour game, which is pretty bad alone, but once you get about half way through the storyline it just gets boring, the levels feel repetative and when you get it handed to you by that one shotgunner who spawned right behind you, you get pretty bored of doing the same thing over and over until finally you kill that guy. But let me make it straight, I DO NOT recommend this game, the first half of the storyline is fun, you have poly graphics with an awesome Kill Bill thing going on, but then you start getting to the (Spoiler alert) Core Levels which is just a more annoying and game-slowing filler. Not to mention how sometimes shotgun rounds that hit wont actually kill your enemy, and other times shotgun rounds from enemies can go straight through corners of walls and objects, the (spoiler alert again) body switch or HotSwitch is pretty fun at first but then they start all the core crap and basically hang the abilty over your head like a parent buying their kid a present only to take it out of the box and dangle it over them just far enough out of reach, and after a while the actual story becomes a joke and you dont even know why superhot.exe is telling you to HotSwitch the core, and the access is denied, not to mention why other options in the menu show that superhot.exe is a game made in 2015, but the ""system"" tells you that your not playing a game, then you punch yourself in the face while in game and it actually hurts your 'real self' which is a guy in a VR Headset playing superhot, like I said, it becomes a joke. The ability to punch a guy, take his gun, shoot his friend, then smash his face in with it is cool, but I feel the potential was wasted here, they came up with a whole new concept which I loved at first, but it feels like they just came up with a lazy, unorganized trailer of ideas, smashed them together then put the Kill Bill style in like a cherry on top. A cherry that sadly sunk to the bottom of the crap sundae."
